WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.910 --> 00:00:06.874 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:06.874 --> 00:00:09.329 align:middle line:90%


00:00:09.329 --> 00:00:11.293 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:11.293 --> 00:00:19.640 align:middle line:90%


00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:21.604 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:21.604 --> 00:00:22.030 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.030 --> 00:00:24.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: We've all
heard the adage, the only

00:00:24.030 --> 00:00:26.070 align:middle line:90%
constant in life is change.

00:00:26.070 --> 00:00:29.880 align:middle line:84%
And most of us are surprised or
frustrated when change happens.

00:00:29.880 --> 00:00:33.570 align:middle line:84%
In this ever-shifting economic
and technological landscape,

00:00:33.570 --> 00:00:36.060 align:middle line:84%
it's become crucial to
learn the skills needed

00:00:36.060 --> 00:00:38.790 align:middle line:84%
to adapt when change
happens, whether it's

00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:42.540 align:middle line:84%
a sudden job loss, or
an unexpected accident,

00:00:42.540 --> 00:00:44.560 align:middle line:90%
or a difficult breakup.

00:00:44.560 --> 00:00:45.360 align:middle line:10%
Hi.

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:48.120 align:middle line:10%
I'm Lisa Garr, and joining
me is career success coach

00:00:48.120 --> 00:00:52.080 align:middle line:10%
and bestselling author Tama
Kieves, who knows firsthand

00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:55.590 align:middle line:10%
the fear and paralysis that
accompanies drastic life

00:00:55.590 --> 00:00:56.700 align:middle line:10%
changes.

00:00:56.700 --> 00:00:59.070 align:middle line:10%
Tama talks about her
journey in her latest book,

00:00:59.070 --> 00:01:00.990 align:middle line:10%
"Thriving Through Uncertainty--

00:01:00.990 --> 00:01:03.300 align:middle line:10%
Moving Beyond Fear
of the Unknown

00:01:03.300 --> 00:01:05.099 align:middle line:10%
and Making Change Work."

00:01:05.099 --> 00:01:06.330 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for joining me.

00:01:06.330 --> 00:01:07.288 align:middle line:90%
>>TAMA KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:01:07.288 --> 00:01:08.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow, what a story.

00:01:08.580 --> 00:01:09.900 align:middle line:90%
My goodness.

00:01:09.900 --> 00:01:12.060 align:middle line:84%
So first of all,
you went to Harvard

00:01:12.060 --> 00:01:14.350 align:middle line:90%
and you graduated with honors?

00:01:14.350 --> 00:01:15.150 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:16.450 align:middle line:90%
From Harvard Law School.

00:01:16.450 --> 00:01:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And I'm a perfect example
of resisting change.

00:01:21.210 --> 00:01:23.700 align:middle line:10%
Like you said in the beginning
of-- just resisting change,

00:01:23.700 --> 00:01:24.500 align:middle line:10%
or--

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:25.590 align:middle line:10%
we always want to be safe.

00:01:25.590 --> 00:01:27.280 align:middle line:10%
We always want to be secure.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:28.950 align:middle line:10%
We always want to
do the right thing.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:32.310 align:middle line:10%
And when I was younger, I
knew that I wanted to write.

00:01:32.310 --> 00:01:34.180 align:middle line:90%
That was my dream.

00:01:34.180 --> 00:01:36.090 align:middle line:84%
But I grew up in
Brooklyn, New York,

00:01:36.090 --> 00:01:39.900 align:middle line:84%
to an orthodox Jewish
family, and writing was not

00:01:39.900 --> 00:01:41.010 align:middle line:90%
a safe path.

00:01:41.010 --> 00:01:41.810 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:01:41.810 --> 00:01:42.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Write?

00:01:42.040 --> 00:01:42.930 align:middle line:90%
What does that mean, anyway?

00:01:42.930 --> 00:01:43.540 align:middle line:90%
You want to write?

00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:43.950 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I want to--

00:01:43.950 --> 00:01:45.450 align:middle line:84%
exact-- that's
basically what I got.

00:01:45.450 --> 00:01:46.510 align:middle line:90%
You're going to write?

00:01:46.510 --> 00:01:48.427 align:middle line:84%
You're going to starve,
you're going to write.

00:01:48.427 --> 00:01:50.670 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS] Right,
because what does that mean?

00:01:50.670 --> 00:01:51.470 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:01:51.470 --> 00:01:54.220 align:middle line:84%
They just-- it didn't
sound like a career path.

00:01:54.220 --> 00:01:55.530 align:middle line:90%
It sounded like a hobby.

00:01:55.530 --> 00:02:00.330 align:middle line:84%
And I ignored that desire,
like so many people,

00:02:00.330 --> 00:02:03.270 align:middle line:84%
and I did what is
"safe" or practical.

00:02:03.270 --> 00:02:05.022 align:middle line:84%
And I went off to
law school instead,

00:02:05.022 --> 00:02:07.230 align:middle line:84%
and to Harvard Law School,
and graduated with honors.

00:02:07.230 --> 00:02:09.950 align:middle line:84%
And I was on partnership
track in a major law firm.

00:02:09.950 --> 00:02:10.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:02:10.750 --> 00:02:14.700 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And like so many
people, I was just miserable.

00:02:14.700 --> 00:02:15.685 align:middle line:90%
I was empty.

00:02:15.685 --> 00:02:18.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But I have to ask you,
how did your parents feel?

00:02:18.060 --> 00:02:18.330 align:middle line:90%
I mean--

00:02:18.330 --> 00:02:19.130 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:02:19.130 --> 00:02:22.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --here you are as
proud parents of a graduated--

00:02:22.500 --> 00:02:23.758 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Very proud parents.

00:02:23.758 --> 00:02:25.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And the
money that it takes--

00:02:25.300 --> 00:02:28.280 align:middle line:84%
oh, and we have some photos
here of you graduating.

00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:29.080 align:middle line:90%
I'm a parent.

00:02:29.080 --> 00:02:30.390 align:middle line:90%
I would've been proud of you.

00:02:30.390 --> 00:02:30.905 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Oh, yes.

00:02:30.905 --> 00:02:31.822 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What happened?

00:02:31.822 --> 00:02:34.260 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: My mother was
bragging in every synagogue,

00:02:34.260 --> 00:02:35.700 align:middle line:90%
for all she was worth.

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:36.900 align:middle line:90%
My little girl.

00:02:36.900 --> 00:02:37.980 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to tell you.

00:02:37.980 --> 00:02:39.360 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:02:39.360 --> 00:02:40.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Sure.

00:02:40.280 --> 00:02:43.320 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: They were horrified,
because I at one point

00:02:43.320 --> 00:02:45.780 align:middle line:90%
just walked out of everything.

00:02:45.780 --> 00:02:47.970 align:middle line:90%
I just walked out of everything.

00:02:47.970 --> 00:02:51.330 align:middle line:84%
Which by the way, you
will do, or you may

00:02:51.330 --> 00:02:53.397 align:middle line:90%
do, if you're unhappy enough.

00:02:53.397 --> 00:02:54.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: If you are fed up.

00:02:54.480 --> 00:02:57.210 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I was just so
unhappy, and I was dying.

00:02:57.210 --> 00:02:59.580 align:middle line:84%
And thank god somebody said
something amazing to me.

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:01.290 align:middle line:90%
He said, think about it.

00:03:01.290 --> 00:03:03.180 align:middle line:84%
If you've been this
successful doing

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:04.340 align:middle line:90%
something you don't love--

00:03:04.340 --> 00:03:05.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]
That's a great--

00:03:05.560 --> 00:03:06.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: What could you
do with what you love?

00:03:06.780 --> 00:03:07.080 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:03:07.080 --> 00:03:08.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Great point.

00:03:08.260 --> 00:03:09.760 align:middle line:84%
I always wonder,
though, when people

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:11.070 align:middle line:90%
want to make a drastic change.

00:03:11.070 --> 00:03:13.093 align:middle line:84%
You never have everything
happen all at once.

00:03:13.093 --> 00:03:15.510 align:middle line:84%
It's this thing and then the
next thing, and it surmounts.

00:03:15.510 --> 00:03:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:03:16.220 --> 00:03:16.540 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:03:16.540 --> 00:03:17.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And you want to escape.

00:03:17.520 --> 00:03:18.780 align:middle line:90%
You want to just leave it all.

00:03:18.780 --> 00:03:19.290 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:03:19.290 --> 00:03:20.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Some people do that.

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:22.080 align:middle line:84%
They just cold turkey
and leave it all.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:22.980 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:03:22.980 --> 00:03:23.910 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or you stay.

00:03:23.910 --> 00:03:25.522 align:middle line:90%
There's no easy way to do it.

00:03:25.522 --> 00:03:27.480 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And I am so
glad you brought that up,

00:03:27.480 --> 00:03:30.060 align:middle line:84%
because I don't think there's
a right way or a wrong way

00:03:30.060 --> 00:03:31.230 align:middle line:90%
to do it.

00:03:31.230 --> 00:03:34.320 align:middle line:84%
The problem is, everybody is
looking for the perfect answer.

00:03:34.320 --> 00:03:36.510 align:middle line:84%
Or you read self-help books
and they're like, well,

00:03:36.510 --> 00:03:38.640 align:middle line:84%
she did this extreme thing, so
I should do the extreme thing.

00:03:38.640 --> 00:03:39.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:41.133 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And when I'm
working with clients,

00:03:41.133 --> 00:03:43.950 align:middle line:84%
everybody has their own
chemistry, their own way,

00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:45.450 align:middle line:90%
and for those of--

00:03:45.450 --> 00:03:49.500 align:middle line:84%
I did a drastic change because
I couldn't do it any other way.

00:03:49.500 --> 00:03:50.850 align:middle line:90%
I was dying.

00:03:50.850 --> 00:03:51.960 align:middle line:90%
I had to get out.

00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:54.210 align:middle line:84%
If you can do it another
way-- if you can do something

00:03:54.210 --> 00:03:56.820 align:middle line:84%
on the side or
experiment, why not?

00:03:56.820 --> 00:03:59.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you got
a job at a law firm.

00:03:59.170 --> 00:03:59.970 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:03:59.970 --> 00:04:01.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you're
working at the law firm.

00:04:01.530 --> 00:04:02.790 align:middle line:90%
Did you get to write there?

00:04:02.790 --> 00:04:04.488 align:middle line:84%
Did you get to express
yourself at all?

00:04:04.488 --> 00:04:06.780 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS] That's
a-- you sound like my mother.

00:04:06.780 --> 00:04:07.186 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:04:07.186 --> 00:04:07.592 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:04:07.592 --> 00:04:08.000 align:middle line:90%
Sorry.

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:09.270 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I'm teasing you.

00:04:09.270 --> 00:04:10.590 align:middle line:84%
Because she was
like, you're writing.

00:04:10.590 --> 00:04:11.507 align:middle line:90%
You're writing briefs.

00:04:11.507 --> 00:04:15.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's like-- but it's
almost like saying to Picasso,

00:04:15.690 --> 00:04:17.730 align:middle line:84%
who's painting garages
or something-- well,

00:04:17.730 --> 00:04:18.700 align:middle line:90%
you're painting!

00:04:18.700 --> 00:04:19.500 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:04:19.500 --> 00:04:20.376 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:04:20.376 --> 00:04:22.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:04:22.440 --> 00:04:25.620 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Being a lawyer was
such a different modality,

00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:28.073 align:middle line:84%
and it was such a different--
it was linear thought.

00:04:28.073 --> 00:04:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
wrong with it.

00:04:29.490 --> 00:04:32.410 align:middle line:84%
It was just that I had this
creative impulse in me--

00:04:32.410 --> 00:04:34.720 align:middle line:84%
this desire to be
something else.

00:04:34.720 --> 00:04:38.400 align:middle line:84%
And if you're doing work that
really isn't what you love,

00:04:38.400 --> 00:04:40.590 align:middle line:90%
it can take more of your energy.

00:04:40.590 --> 00:04:42.270 align:middle line:90%
It can exhaust you.

00:04:42.270 --> 00:04:44.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So do you
use your lawyer

00:04:44.790 --> 00:04:48.000 align:middle line:84%
energy or that analytical
energy in what you do now?

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:49.590 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: In some ways, yes.

00:04:49.590 --> 00:04:52.473 align:middle line:84%
I always tell my clients,
I'm like your advocate.

00:04:52.473 --> 00:04:54.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm no longer a lawyer,
but I'm your advocate.

00:04:54.390 --> 00:04:56.250 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to prove
the case of you.

00:04:56.250 --> 00:04:57.700 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to prove
your potential.

00:04:57.700 --> 00:04:58.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:04:58.500 --> 00:04:59.280 align:middle line:90%
That's great.

00:04:59.280 --> 00:05:00.738 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And I
think the other way

00:05:00.738 --> 00:05:04.470 align:middle line:84%
I use it is it gives me
credibility, because I

00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:07.380 align:middle line:84%
am about following an inspired
path-- the path of genius,

00:05:07.380 --> 00:05:10.800 align:middle line:84%
listening to an inner
voice, and being visionary.

00:05:10.800 --> 00:05:14.660 align:middle line:84%
And it just gives it
credibility that I have made it

00:05:14.660 --> 00:05:16.150 align:middle line:90%
in the, quote, "real world."

00:05:16.150 --> 00:05:18.240 align:middle line:84%
And I have found a different
kind of power to use.

00:05:18.240 --> 00:05:18.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:19.310 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:05:19.310 --> 00:05:21.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And for anyone
who is in that place,

00:05:21.210 --> 00:05:25.700 align:middle line:84%
that is in that dead
end, non-creative space,

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:29.075 align:middle line:84%
they want to make a change,
what would you suggest?

00:05:29.075 --> 00:05:31.450 align:middle line:84%
Rather than-- well, would you
shock your family in saying

00:05:31.450 --> 00:05:32.090 align:middle line:90%
I'm leaving you.

00:05:32.090 --> 00:05:32.630 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Just
shock your family.

00:05:32.630 --> 00:05:33.110 align:middle line:90%
It's fun.

00:05:33.110 --> 00:05:34.070 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:05:34.070 --> 00:05:35.030 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]
That's a great--

00:05:35.030 --> 00:05:35.593 align:middle line:90%
I did it.

00:05:35.593 --> 00:05:36.393 align:middle line:90%
You can too.

00:05:36.393 --> 00:05:37.910 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: You can too.

00:05:37.910 --> 00:05:39.470 align:middle line:84%
Send them to therapy
for a change.

00:05:39.470 --> 00:05:40.270 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:05:40.270 --> 00:05:41.220 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:05:41.220 --> 00:05:42.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You do it.

00:05:42.020 --> 00:05:43.280 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:05:43.280 --> 00:05:45.440 align:middle line:84%
I think the main
thing that I would say

00:05:45.440 --> 00:05:48.170 align:middle line:90%
is just start experimenting--

00:05:48.170 --> 00:05:51.230 align:middle line:84%
that you don't have to make
any huge change right away.

00:05:51.230 --> 00:05:53.990 align:middle line:84%
Of that again, everybody has
their path and their way.

00:05:53.990 --> 00:05:56.510 align:middle line:84%
I believe a path is
already inside you.

00:05:56.510 --> 00:05:58.670 align:middle line:84%
And so I would just
want you to experiment.

00:05:58.670 --> 00:06:00.395 align:middle line:84%
Because some people think, oh,
I want to be a photographer,

00:06:00.395 --> 00:06:02.150 align:middle line:84%
or I want to be a this,
or I want to be a that.

00:06:02.150 --> 00:06:02.282 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:06:02.282 --> 00:06:04.370 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: How about you
experimenting a little bit

00:06:04.370 --> 00:06:06.200 align:middle line:90%
before you go jump off a cliff?

00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:07.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Join a club.

00:06:07.100 --> 00:06:08.350 align:middle line:90%
Do something as a hobby first.

00:06:08.350 --> 00:06:09.150 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:06:09.150 --> 00:06:10.010 align:middle line:90%
Take a class.

00:06:10.010 --> 00:06:10.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:11.110 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: You know?

00:06:11.110 --> 00:06:13.370 align:middle line:84%
You can do something
on a Wednesday night.

00:06:13.370 --> 00:06:16.010 align:middle line:90%
You don't have to quit your job.

00:06:16.010 --> 00:06:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But for those who
want to take that leap

00:06:18.470 --> 00:06:22.880 align:middle line:84%
and take that risk,
is there an easy way?

00:06:22.880 --> 00:06:24.470 align:middle line:84%
I guess easy is
not the right word.

00:06:24.470 --> 00:06:28.880 align:middle line:84%
Is there another way to do
it that's gentler on yourself

00:06:28.880 --> 00:06:30.620 align:middle line:90%
and your loved ones?

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:31.970 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I wish there was.

00:06:31.970 --> 00:06:33.800 align:middle line:84%
Certainly if you're
conscious enough

00:06:33.800 --> 00:06:36.030 align:middle line:84%
where you can have that
great communication, sure.

00:06:36.030 --> 00:06:41.330 align:middle line:84%
But to make a change like that,
at least for me, I was dying.

00:06:41.330 --> 00:06:43.220 align:middle line:90%
I was out of my mind in pain.

00:06:43.220 --> 00:06:47.063 align:middle line:84%
I was in depression of, I
didn't want to make this change.

00:06:47.063 --> 00:06:48.980 align:middle line:84%
I didn't consciously
want to make this change.

00:06:48.980 --> 00:06:51.420 align:middle line:84%
I put a lot of investment
into doing this.

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:55.310 align:middle line:84%
And that path seemed secure,
and that path seemed reasonable,

00:06:55.310 --> 00:06:56.330 align:middle line:90%
and it was kind of fun.

00:06:56.330 --> 00:06:58.460 align:middle line:84%
You say you're a Harvard
lawyer, everybody respects you.

00:06:58.460 --> 00:06:59.960 align:middle line:84%
You say you're a
poet, not so much.

00:06:59.960 --> 00:07:00.820 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] You know?

00:07:00.820 --> 00:07:01.010 align:middle line:90%
And so--

00:07:01.010 --> 00:07:01.280 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:07:01.280 --> 00:07:02.000 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:03.375 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I did
not-- every fiber

00:07:03.375 --> 00:07:05.690 align:middle line:84%
of my being on some
level, or my mind,

00:07:05.690 --> 00:07:07.710 align:middle line:84%
did not want to
make that change.

00:07:07.710 --> 00:07:10.430 align:middle line:84%
But my soul, my gut,
my heart, my genius,

00:07:10.430 --> 00:07:13.280 align:middle line:90%
something else beyond me did.

00:07:13.280 --> 00:07:17.810 align:middle line:84%
And so at the time, it
is a little cataclysmic.

00:07:17.810 --> 00:07:19.340 align:middle line:90%
There is a grieving process.

00:07:19.340 --> 00:07:22.700 align:middle line:84%
Like one life or one
identity is leaving.

00:07:22.700 --> 00:07:23.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:07:23.500 --> 00:07:25.260 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And again,
everybody does it differently.

00:07:25.260 --> 00:07:27.195 align:middle line:84%
Some people might
find an amalgam of it.

00:07:27.195 --> 00:07:28.820 align:middle line:84%
Some people might
find a different way.

00:07:28.820 --> 00:07:30.237 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you
hang up the suits?

00:07:30.237 --> 00:07:31.335 align:middle line:90%
Did you donate them?

00:07:31.335 --> 00:07:32.710 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I burned
the pantyhose.

00:07:32.710 --> 00:07:33.522 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:07:33.522 --> 00:07:34.406 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You did?

00:07:34.406 --> 00:07:35.290 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I did.

00:07:35.290 --> 00:07:36.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You had a ceremony.

00:07:36.120 --> 00:07:36.530 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:07:36.530 --> 00:07:38.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's
interesting, though.

00:07:38.060 --> 00:07:40.980 align:middle line:84%
Because you let go
what wasn't working.

00:07:40.980 --> 00:07:41.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:07:41.780 --> 00:07:46.310 align:middle line:84%
And I will say-- and just
to be clear, when I left,

00:07:46.310 --> 00:07:48.290 align:middle line:90%
I was not clear that that's it.

00:07:48.290 --> 00:07:49.840 align:middle line:90%
I'm leaving forever.

00:07:49.840 --> 00:07:51.230 align:middle line:90%
This is it.

00:07:51.230 --> 00:07:52.730 align:middle line:90%
It was a next step.

00:07:52.730 --> 00:07:55.970 align:middle line:84%
It was oh, my god,
I am dying here.

00:07:55.970 --> 00:08:00.830 align:middle line:84%
And I was literally in therapy,
and I literally at one point

00:08:00.830 --> 00:08:03.540 align:middle line:84%
was considering at some
point ending my life.

00:08:03.540 --> 00:08:04.903 align:middle line:90%
I was so depressed.

00:08:04.903 --> 00:08:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And I was talking
to the therapist

00:08:06.320 --> 00:08:07.490 align:middle line:90%
about not wanting to live.

00:08:07.490 --> 00:08:10.670 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, you
could leave your job.

00:08:10.670 --> 00:08:12.150 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
leave the planet.

00:08:12.150 --> 00:08:12.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:08:12.950 --> 00:08:15.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And that had
not occurred to me.

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:16.450 align:middle line:90%
That had not occurred to me.

00:08:16.450 --> 00:08:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:08:17.250 --> 00:08:19.617 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I was so in
that culture of success.

00:08:19.617 --> 00:08:21.200 align:middle line:84%
And this is the hoop
you jump through.

00:08:21.200 --> 00:08:21.740 align:middle line:90%
You do this.

00:08:21.740 --> 00:08:23.090 align:middle line:90%
You get an A. You get a bonus.

00:08:23.090 --> 00:08:23.960 align:middle line:90%
You perform.

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:25.580 align:middle line:84%
You do what
everybody else wants.

00:08:25.580 --> 00:08:28.280 align:middle line:84%
It never even occurred to
me that it was a valid path

00:08:28.280 --> 00:08:29.930 align:middle line:90%
to do what I wanted.

00:08:29.930 --> 00:08:31.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: A, support
groups are amazing.

00:08:31.820 --> 00:08:35.780 align:middle line:84%
Therapy, friends, people you
can have around you even when

00:08:35.780 --> 00:08:37.070 align:middle line:90%
there are so many that say--

00:08:37.070 --> 00:08:37.870 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:08:37.870 --> 00:08:38.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:38.270 --> 00:08:39.950 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's a
really key point.

00:08:39.950 --> 00:08:42.720 align:middle line:84%
That's one of the main
reasons I do the work I do.

00:08:42.720 --> 00:08:46.010 align:middle line:84%
That's why I wrote my books is,
I want my books and my words

00:08:46.010 --> 00:08:48.350 align:middle line:84%
to be the something
that somebody can put

00:08:48.350 --> 00:08:51.230 align:middle line:84%
in their pocket that
guides them so they never

00:08:51.230 --> 00:08:52.390 align:middle line:90%
have to do it alone.

00:08:52.390 --> 00:08:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's the support--

00:08:52.520 --> 00:08:55.240 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And there are so many
resources now, thank god, and--

00:08:55.240 --> 00:08:56.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:08:56.040 --> 00:08:58.310 align:middle line:84%
And then on the other
side, if you were a parent

00:08:58.310 --> 00:09:02.960 align:middle line:84%
and you see this culture of kids
who are taking Adderall to keep

00:09:02.960 --> 00:09:04.910 align:middle line:84%
up, and the learning
curve goes up,

00:09:04.910 --> 00:09:08.450 align:middle line:84%
and the stress, and
these standardized tests,

00:09:08.450 --> 00:09:10.520 align:middle line:90%
what would you tell them?

00:09:10.520 --> 00:09:15.590 align:middle line:84%
There is no "follow your
dream" category in college.

00:09:15.590 --> 00:09:18.020 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And I think that's
a really hard thing, that I

00:09:18.020 --> 00:09:22.440 align:middle line:84%
think for parents, it's undoing
our usual way of thinking.

00:09:22.440 --> 00:09:24.270 align:middle line:90%
We learned, be a doctor.

00:09:24.270 --> 00:09:25.070 align:middle line:90%
Be a lawyer.

00:09:25.070 --> 00:09:25.790 align:middle line:90%
Be a professional.

00:09:25.790 --> 00:09:26.300 align:middle line:90%
Be a this.

00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:27.300 align:middle line:90%
Make money.

00:09:27.300 --> 00:09:29.350 align:middle line:84%
Make money is the
source of success.

00:09:29.350 --> 00:09:34.220 align:middle line:84%
And I want to educate people
that happiness and health

00:09:34.220 --> 00:09:37.370 align:middle line:84%
and doing your right life
is your greatest success.

00:09:37.370 --> 00:09:40.130 align:middle line:84%
And so as a parent,
maybe it is, you're

00:09:40.130 --> 00:09:43.010 align:middle line:84%
giving your kid permission
to find their genius--

00:09:43.010 --> 00:09:43.940 align:middle line:90%
their talent.

00:09:43.940 --> 00:09:46.400 align:middle line:84%
And that might mean
experimenting a little bit.

00:09:46.400 --> 00:09:47.870 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, let's talk
about the money, though.

00:09:47.870 --> 00:09:48.380 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:09:48.380 --> 00:09:49.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So?

00:09:49.070 --> 00:09:50.090 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Let's talk
about the money.

00:09:50.090 --> 00:09:51.200 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:09:51.200 --> 00:09:52.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Did it follow you?

00:09:52.650 --> 00:09:53.450 align:middle line:90%
What did you do?

00:09:53.450 --> 00:09:55.370 align:middle line:84%
You were making a--
probably a great living.

00:09:55.370 --> 00:09:55.960 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:09:55.960 --> 00:09:56.210 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:09:56.210 --> 00:09:57.835 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What did you
do about running--

00:09:57.835 --> 00:10:00.050 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: The money
is a terrifying piece.

00:10:00.050 --> 00:10:02.900 align:middle line:84%
Of course it is, especially
when we live in this culture.

00:10:02.900 --> 00:10:05.250 align:middle line:84%
But one of the things I
always tell my clients,

00:10:05.250 --> 00:10:07.250 align:middle line:84%
and one of the things
that I learned personally,

00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:11.640 align:middle line:84%
was as much as you think you
want money, you want security.

00:10:11.640 --> 00:10:13.960 align:middle line:84%
You want to know that
you're going to be OK.

00:10:13.960 --> 00:10:14.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:10:14.240 --> 00:10:15.823 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's
really what you want.

00:10:15.823 --> 00:10:19.680 align:middle line:84%
And what I learned the hard way
is that health is your greatest

00:10:19.680 --> 00:10:20.670 align:middle line:90%
security.

00:10:20.670 --> 00:10:22.290 align:middle line:90%
Health is your greate--

00:10:22.290 --> 00:10:25.330 align:middle line:84%
I was making a great
living and I was dying.

00:10:25.330 --> 00:10:28.110 align:middle line:84%
And I have a lot of clients
who make a lot of money,

00:10:28.110 --> 00:10:29.558 align:middle line:90%
and they've got health risks.

00:10:29.558 --> 00:10:32.100 align:middle line:84%
And at that point, all the money
in the world won't save you.

00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:32.900 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:10:32.900 --> 00:10:34.860 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so for me,
the greatest security,

00:10:34.860 --> 00:10:38.940 align:middle line:84%
first and foremost, is doing
what you came here to do.

00:10:38.940 --> 00:10:40.420 align:middle line:90%
And to your point about--

00:10:40.420 --> 00:10:40.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:10:40.500 --> 00:10:42.583 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: OK, OK, but how
do you pay the mortgage?

00:10:42.583 --> 00:10:44.760 align:middle line:84%
Or how do you pay
for the apartment?

00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:46.440 align:middle line:90%
It's not an either/or.

00:10:46.440 --> 00:10:49.110 align:middle line:84%
It's not like you
have to do one thing.

00:10:49.110 --> 00:10:51.520 align:middle line:84%
That again, you
might do many thi--

00:10:51.520 --> 00:10:54.780 align:middle line:84%
you might do different
things on the side.

00:10:54.780 --> 00:10:57.260 align:middle line:84%
There's a beautiful
term in the literature--

00:10:57.260 --> 00:10:59.640 align:middle line:84%
it's my favorite
term, and it's called

00:10:59.640 --> 00:11:01.990 align:middle line:90%
"multiple streams of income."

00:11:01.990 --> 00:11:02.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:02.790 --> 00:11:03.748 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: All the love.

00:11:03.748 --> 00:11:05.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, this is what
we're heading towards.

00:11:05.810 --> 00:11:08.760 align:middle line:84%
You've got the Gen X, Y,
Z, and every generation

00:11:08.760 --> 00:11:10.830 align:middle line:84%
is now either
getting a side hustle

00:11:10.830 --> 00:11:13.797 align:middle line:84%
or some type of entrepreneurial
spirit is happening.

00:11:13.797 --> 00:11:14.880 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: And it needs to.

00:11:14.880 --> 00:11:16.845 align:middle line:90%
Our culture is changing so much.

00:11:16.845 --> 00:11:20.220 align:middle line:84%
What used to be the
track of security

00:11:20.220 --> 00:11:21.840 align:middle line:90%
is no longer a competitive edge.

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:22.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:11:22.110 --> 00:11:24.235 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Companies want
to see that you're adept--

00:11:24.235 --> 00:11:25.800 align:middle line:84%
abdapta-- I can't
even say the word.

00:11:25.800 --> 00:11:26.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:26.130 --> 00:11:26.430 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Adaptable.

00:11:26.430 --> 00:11:27.340 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] You know?

00:11:27.340 --> 00:11:27.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:27.560 --> 00:11:28.020 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:11:28.020 --> 00:11:30.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: They want to see that
you can do different things.

00:11:30.570 --> 00:11:31.680 align:middle line:90%
Everything's changing.

00:11:31.680 --> 00:11:33.690 align:middle line:90%
It's no longer one track.

00:11:33.690 --> 00:11:35.640 align:middle line:84%
And so what we
used to maybe think

00:11:35.640 --> 00:11:39.450 align:middle line:84%
was erratic or not
focused, I think

00:11:39.450 --> 00:11:42.030 align:middle line:84%
now is multi-talented
or multi-passionate.

00:11:42.030 --> 00:11:43.890 align:middle line:84%
And you're going to use
different strengths.

00:11:43.890 --> 00:11:44.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, look.

00:11:44.690 --> 00:11:45.720 align:middle line:90%
You are a great example.

00:11:45.720 --> 00:11:46.860 align:middle line:90%
You wanted to be a writer.

00:11:46.860 --> 00:11:47.220 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:11:47.220 --> 00:11:49.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But you probably
make your money as a coach.

00:11:49.320 --> 00:11:50.280 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Exac-- you know--

00:11:50.280 --> 00:11:50.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:11:50.490 --> 00:11:52.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And when
I started writing,

00:11:52.200 --> 00:11:54.480 align:middle line:84%
I realized I wanted to
be around other writers,

00:11:54.480 --> 00:11:56.190 align:middle line:84%
and so I started
a support group.

00:11:56.190 --> 00:11:57.750 align:middle line:84%
And people said,
oh my god, you're

00:11:57.750 --> 00:11:59.310 align:middle line:90%
good at speaking or teaching.

00:11:59.310 --> 00:12:00.663 align:middle line:90%
And so I started teaching.

00:12:00.663 --> 00:12:02.580 align:middle line:84%
And then when I started
teaching, people said,

00:12:02.580 --> 00:12:03.870 align:middle line:90%
would you ever lead retreats?

00:12:03.870 --> 00:12:05.880 align:middle line:84%
And so I started
leading retreats.

00:12:05.880 --> 00:12:08.520 align:middle line:84%
And people started asking me
to work individually with them.

00:12:08.520 --> 00:12:10.520 align:middle line:84%
And so-- before coaching
was even a living.

00:12:10.520 --> 00:12:11.320 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:12:11.320 --> 00:12:13.590 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so I make my
money in li-- going back

00:12:13.590 --> 00:12:15.450 align:middle line:90%
to that multiple income streams.

00:12:15.450 --> 00:12:16.890 align:middle line:90%
I make my money as a coach.

00:12:16.890 --> 00:12:18.330 align:middle line:90%
I make my money as a speaker.

00:12:18.330 --> 00:12:20.190 align:middle line:90%
I make my money as an author.

00:12:20.190 --> 00:12:22.260 align:middle line:90%
I make my money doing retreats.

00:12:22.260 --> 00:12:24.592 align:middle line:84%
Some months, I'm not making
as much money speaking,

00:12:24.592 --> 00:12:26.050 align:middle line:84%
but I'm making more
money coaching.

00:12:26.050 --> 00:12:28.375 align:middle line:84%
Some months, coaching is
down, but writing is up.

00:12:28.375 --> 00:12:30.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So one thing
leads to the next,

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:32.310 align:middle line:84%
as long as you just
take the first step.

00:12:32.310 --> 00:12:35.130 align:middle line:84%
And this also applies to someone
who is maybe being laid off,

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:37.650 align:middle line:84%
or it's not their
choice to go and find--

00:12:37.650 --> 00:12:42.330 align:middle line:84%
you've got that mourning
period of losing your job

00:12:42.330 --> 00:12:44.710 align:middle line:84%
and dealing with that, and
having to pick yourself up

00:12:44.710 --> 00:12:45.510 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:12:45.510 --> 00:12:46.310 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:12:46.310 --> 00:12:48.120 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So is it
one step at a time?

00:12:48.120 --> 00:12:49.455 align:middle line:90%
Is that how you're done this?

00:12:49.455 --> 00:12:51.330 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's the
only way that I know it.

00:12:51.330 --> 00:12:52.747 align:middle line:84%
In "Thriving Through
Uncertainty,"

00:12:52.747 --> 00:12:55.500 align:middle line:84%
I have a whole chapter on
following the breadcrumbs.

00:12:55.500 --> 00:12:57.000 align:middle line:90%
Just following the breadcrumbs.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:12:58.500 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's looking
for the master

00:12:58.500 --> 00:12:59.623 align:middle line:90%
plan and their whole life.

00:12:59.623 --> 00:13:01.540 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to figure
out their whole life.

00:13:01.540 --> 00:13:04.050 align:middle line:84%
OK, if I'm this age
and I have this, that,

00:13:04.050 --> 00:13:05.340 align:middle line:90%
and I have this whatever.

00:13:05.340 --> 00:13:07.170 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm going
to ask you to do

00:13:07.170 --> 00:13:10.260 align:middle line:84%
is follow what's
speaking to you now.

00:13:10.260 --> 00:13:11.700 align:middle line:90%
What do you love now?

00:13:11.700 --> 00:13:13.920 align:middle line:90%
What's moving you now?

00:13:13.920 --> 00:13:16.730 align:middle line:84%
But to your point of
when you get laid off--

00:13:16.730 --> 00:13:17.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:13:17.530 --> 00:13:17.910 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right?

00:13:17.910 --> 00:13:18.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:13:18.300 --> 00:13:20.258 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Everybody
immediately thinks OK, I've

00:13:20.258 --> 00:13:21.850 align:middle line:90%
got to jump into that next job.

00:13:21.850 --> 00:13:27.210 align:middle line:84%
But there is that moment of
grieving or sadness or fear.

00:13:27.210 --> 00:13:30.040 align:middle line:84%
And I think everybody wants
to know, what do I do?

00:13:30.040 --> 00:13:31.210 align:middle line:90%
What do I do?

00:13:31.210 --> 00:13:34.500 align:middle line:84%
I think it's a path of
undoing and undoing.

00:13:34.500 --> 00:13:38.040 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by that
is undoing the fears,

00:13:38.040 --> 00:13:42.000 align:middle line:84%
undoing all the horrible
stories you're telling yourself.

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:45.780 align:middle line:84%
Because what happens is when
you're in fear and anxiety,

00:13:45.780 --> 00:13:49.080 align:middle line:90%
you can't hear inspiration.

00:13:49.080 --> 00:13:51.930 align:middle line:84%
You can't be listening to
inspiration and guidance

00:13:51.930 --> 00:13:53.790 align:middle line:84%
and fear and anxiety
at the same time.

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:57.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, it is the common
default mechanism of change.

00:13:57.400 --> 00:13:58.200 align:middle line:90%
Fear is.

00:13:58.200 --> 00:13:59.000 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Sure is.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:13:59.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It really is.

00:13:59.970 --> 00:14:04.350 align:middle line:84%
And we get fed so much fear
from various media sources

00:14:04.350 --> 00:14:05.895 align:middle line:84%
that it really is
all about the fear.

00:14:05.895 --> 00:14:07.080 align:middle line:84%
It keeps you on the
edge of the seat,

00:14:07.080 --> 00:14:08.310 align:middle line:90%
and the fear and the fear.

00:14:08.310 --> 00:14:10.660 align:middle line:84%
And talking about thriving
through uncertainty.

00:14:10.660 --> 00:14:12.660 align:middle line:84%
Let's just talk about how
much uncertainty there

00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:13.670 align:middle line:90%
is right now in the world.

00:14:13.670 --> 00:14:13.870 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:14:13.870 --> 00:14:15.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We've got
financial uncertainty.

00:14:15.300 --> 00:14:16.920 align:middle line:84%
We've got environmental
uncertainty.

00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:19.980 align:middle line:84%
We've got relationship
uncertainty,

00:14:19.980 --> 00:14:21.020 align:middle line:90%
religious uncertainty.

00:14:21.020 --> 00:14:21.820 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:14:21.820 --> 00:14:23.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're talking about
thriving through all this?

00:14:23.850 --> 00:14:25.305 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Thriving
through uncertainty.

00:14:25.305 --> 00:14:26.112 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:14:26.112 --> 00:14:27.408 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:14:27.408 --> 00:14:28.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:14:28.560 --> 00:14:29.360 align:middle line:90%
But what's--

00:14:29.360 --> 00:14:32.010 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: First of all, I always
write what I need to learn.

00:14:32.010 --> 00:14:32.810 align:middle line:90%
So full disclosure.

00:14:32.810 --> 00:14:33.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:14:33.610 --> 00:14:35.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I write what
the heck I need to learn.

00:14:35.650 --> 00:14:38.160 align:middle line:84%
And I think the world is
in rock and roll times.

00:14:38.160 --> 00:14:38.980 align:middle line:90%
I really do.

00:14:38.980 --> 00:14:42.400 align:middle line:84%
I think we're in a
wildly different time.

00:14:42.400 --> 00:14:44.552 align:middle line:90%
There's so much going on.

00:14:44.552 --> 00:14:46.260 align:middle line:84%
And so in "Thriving
Through Uncertainty,"

00:14:46.260 --> 00:14:49.830 align:middle line:84%
I talk about how uncertainty
is actually your superpower.

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:51.480 align:middle line:90%
And what I mean by that--

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:53.700 align:middle line:84%
why say it's your
superpower, is when

00:14:53.700 --> 00:14:56.310 align:middle line:84%
all the answers in the world
aren't doing it for you

00:14:56.310 --> 00:14:58.170 align:middle line:90%
anymore, there's no solidity.

00:14:58.170 --> 00:14:59.430 align:middle line:90%
There's no one expert.

00:14:59.430 --> 00:15:01.560 align:middle line:90%
There's no stability.

00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:03.910 align:middle line:84%
Maybe for the first
time, we're going

00:15:03.910 --> 00:15:07.230 align:middle line:84%
to start listening to
ourselves and to our instincts

00:15:07.230 --> 00:15:08.130 align:middle line:90%
and to our genius.

00:15:08.130 --> 00:15:12.580 align:middle line:84%
Because I know-- as a coach, I
know that the path is already

00:15:12.580 --> 00:15:13.380 align:middle line:90%
inside you.

00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:14.940 align:middle line:90%
You already have an answer.

00:15:14.940 --> 00:15:17.250 align:middle line:84%
There is a stability
in each of us.

00:15:17.250 --> 00:15:18.890 align:middle line:90%
It's not external.

00:15:18.890 --> 00:15:21.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's so
interesting, because after you

00:15:21.830 --> 00:15:24.410 align:middle line:84%
have this level of uncertainty,
you feel like playing small.

00:15:24.410 --> 00:15:24.830 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:15:24.830 --> 00:15:25.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Being very contracted.

00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:26.240 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:15:26.240 --> 00:15:28.490 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And I was having
this conversation with myself

00:15:28.490 --> 00:15:30.800 align:middle line:84%
this week of, how
am I going to handle

00:15:30.800 --> 00:15:33.530 align:middle line:84%
all the things I need to handle
from this tiny little box?

00:15:33.530 --> 00:15:34.820 align:middle line:90%
It's just not going to work.

00:15:34.820 --> 00:15:37.430 align:middle line:84%
I have got to expand
myself in order

00:15:37.430 --> 00:15:40.070 align:middle line:84%
to have the capacity to
handle the things that

00:15:40.070 --> 00:15:41.030 align:middle line:90%
are coming at me.

00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:42.488 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, everything
else is going

00:15:42.488 --> 00:15:44.510 align:middle line:90%
to be feeling like a threat.

00:15:44.510 --> 00:15:47.303 align:middle line:84%
I love your reframe of
uncertainty as a superpower.

00:15:47.303 --> 00:15:48.470 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: It's a superpower.

00:15:48.470 --> 00:15:49.852 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's a great reframe.

00:15:49.852 --> 00:15:50.810 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: It really is.

00:15:50.810 --> 00:15:52.430 align:middle line:90%
Because again, we all cringe.

00:15:52.430 --> 00:15:55.310 align:middle line:84%
We all immediately
contract, because we're

00:15:55.310 --> 00:15:57.440 align:middle line:90%
trying to stay in control.

00:15:57.440 --> 00:16:00.500 align:middle line:84%
And a creative,
inspired life, a life

00:16:00.500 --> 00:16:03.560 align:middle line:84%
of being more than you
ever dreamed you could be,

00:16:03.560 --> 00:16:05.305 align:middle line:84%
is not going to
come from control.

00:16:05.305 --> 00:16:06.105 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right?

00:16:06.105 --> 00:16:06.380 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: It's--

00:16:06.380 --> 00:16:08.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or contraction or
playing small, or hiding.

00:16:08.210 --> 00:16:09.320 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Or contraction
or playing small.

00:16:09.320 --> 00:16:09.700 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:16:09.700 --> 00:16:11.408 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And by the
way, sometimes we're

00:16:11.408 --> 00:16:15.340 align:middle line:84%
playing small in a way
that society thinks is big.

00:16:15.340 --> 00:16:16.950 align:middle line:90%
And what I mean by that--

00:16:16.950 --> 00:16:17.750 align:middle line:90%
I like your look.

00:16:17.750 --> 00:16:23.100 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] What I mean by that is
that when I was practicing law,

00:16:23.100 --> 00:16:25.280 align:middle line:84%
everybody thought, oh,
she's in that big time.

00:16:25.280 --> 00:16:26.270 align:middle line:90%
She's playing big.

00:16:26.270 --> 00:16:29.060 align:middle line:84%
That was actually
playing small for me,

00:16:29.060 --> 00:16:31.070 align:middle line:90%
because it wasn't my real dream.

00:16:31.070 --> 00:16:32.540 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't my real self.

00:16:32.540 --> 00:16:34.100 align:middle line:90%
I was playing it safe.

00:16:34.100 --> 00:16:36.890 align:middle line:84%
I was doing what everybody
else thought was OK,

00:16:36.890 --> 00:16:38.070 align:middle line:90%
so that was playing small.

00:16:38.070 --> 00:16:38.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:16:38.870 --> 00:16:41.170 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Playing
big meant I'm going

00:16:41.170 --> 00:16:45.560 align:middle line:84%
to trust my instincts more than
what all the experts tell me.

00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:49.400 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now when you decided
to do that, did you fail?

00:16:49.400 --> 00:16:50.310 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Every day.

00:16:50.310 --> 00:16:51.110 align:middle line:90%
I'm still failing.

00:16:51.110 --> 00:16:51.514 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:16:51.514 --> 00:16:52.322 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right?

00:16:52.322 --> 00:16:53.130 align:middle line:90%
Failing forward.

00:16:53.130 --> 00:16:54.710 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Depending on
what you-- failing forward.

00:16:54.710 --> 00:16:56.240 align:middle line:84%
Depending on what
you call failure.

00:16:56.240 --> 00:16:59.850 align:middle line:84%
And I think failure was
the biggest fear I had,

00:16:59.850 --> 00:17:00.650 align:middle line:90%
of all of them.

00:17:00.650 --> 00:17:02.810 align:middle line:84%
Not even money-- failure
was my biggest fear,

00:17:02.810 --> 00:17:03.980 align:middle line:90%
because it was a--

00:17:03.980 --> 00:17:08.599 align:middle line:84%
I was groomed for success,
and I had this swanky job.

00:17:08.599 --> 00:17:11.690 align:middle line:84%
And I was so afraid that I'm
going to go off to find myself,

00:17:11.690 --> 00:17:14.900 align:middle line:84%
and everybody's going to go, she
should have kept her day job.

00:17:14.900 --> 00:17:17.369 align:middle line:84%
Of just-- I was so
afraid of failure.

00:17:17.369 --> 00:17:21.410 align:middle line:84%
But there was this one fantasy
that kept coming to me of,

00:17:21.410 --> 00:17:22.579 align:middle line:90%
I kept--

00:17:22.579 --> 00:17:25.670 align:middle line:84%
I had this fantasy that
at the end of my own life,

00:17:25.670 --> 00:17:28.670 align:middle line:84%
there would be all these
beings in white robes.

00:17:28.670 --> 00:17:30.380 align:middle line:84%
And they would
show me everything

00:17:30.380 --> 00:17:31.850 align:middle line:90%
my life was meant to be.

00:17:31.850 --> 00:17:34.850 align:middle line:84%
They would show me the final
movie explaining your life.

00:17:34.850 --> 00:17:37.820 align:middle line:84%
And they would show
me here was the books

00:17:37.820 --> 00:17:38.990 align:middle line:90%
you were going to write.

00:17:38.990 --> 00:17:41.180 align:middle line:84%
Here were the people
you were going to help.

00:17:41.180 --> 00:17:42.770 align:middle line:90%
Here was the editors lining up.

00:17:42.770 --> 00:17:43.670 align:middle line:90%
Here was the agent.

00:17:43.670 --> 00:17:45.590 align:middle line:90%
Here was the publisher.

00:17:45.590 --> 00:17:47.810 align:middle line:84%
You weren't meant
to practice law.

00:17:47.810 --> 00:17:51.590 align:middle line:84%
On Sunday nights, when you
were throwing up miserable,

00:17:51.590 --> 00:17:53.210 align:middle line:90%
we thought you knew.

00:17:53.210 --> 00:17:54.890 align:middle line:90%
But no, you had willpower.

00:17:54.890 --> 00:17:56.390 align:middle line:90%
You kept going.

00:17:56.390 --> 00:17:58.070 align:middle line:90%
And I had that fantasy.

00:17:58.070 --> 00:18:00.020 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, oh my god.

00:18:00.020 --> 00:18:01.820 align:middle line:84%
I can't get to
the end of my life

00:18:01.820 --> 00:18:04.490 align:middle line:84%
and realize I could
have been a writer.

00:18:04.490 --> 00:18:05.810 align:middle line:90%
I could have been an author.

00:18:05.810 --> 00:18:07.340 align:middle line:90%
I could have lived my dreams.

00:18:07.340 --> 00:18:09.640 align:middle line:84%
And I was the only
one stopping myself.

00:18:09.640 --> 00:18:12.050 align:middle line:84%
And so I always tell
people that as much

00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:15.530 align:middle line:84%
as you may fear failure, I
think you fear regret more.

00:18:15.530 --> 00:18:16.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:18:16.760 --> 00:18:18.030 align:middle line:90%
That is a great point.

00:18:18.030 --> 00:18:18.830 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:18:18.830 --> 00:18:20.955 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is a great
point, and you definitely--

00:18:20.955 --> 00:18:23.780 align:middle line:84%
that is a great vision too,
because if you didn't see

00:18:23.780 --> 00:18:24.650 align:middle line:90%
that--

00:18:24.650 --> 00:18:25.700 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:18:25.700 --> 00:18:28.120 align:middle line:84%
It was just that thing of,
I can't face my own life

00:18:28.120 --> 00:18:29.690 align:middle line:90%
knowing I didn't even try it.

00:18:29.690 --> 00:18:32.210 align:middle line:84%
It's one thing if you try
it and it doesn't work

00:18:32.210 --> 00:18:34.070 align:middle line:84%
and the world stops
you a million times.

00:18:34.070 --> 00:18:36.620 align:middle line:90%
But to stop ourselves.

00:18:36.620 --> 00:18:37.850 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't bear that.

00:18:37.850 --> 00:18:41.300 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So did you dive
into teaching or learning

00:18:41.300 --> 00:18:42.470 align:middle line:90%
before you became a teacher?

00:18:42.470 --> 00:18:44.660 align:middle line:90%
Did you go through courses?

00:18:44.660 --> 00:18:46.227 align:middle line:90%
Or did you start to study?

00:18:46.227 --> 00:18:47.310 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I am the course.

00:18:47.310 --> 00:18:47.700 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:18:47.700 --> 00:18:48.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:18:48.500 --> 00:18:50.258 align:middle line:90%


00:18:50.258 --> 00:18:51.800 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: There is
that adage of "you

00:18:51.800 --> 00:18:53.045 align:middle line:90%
teach what you need to learn."

00:18:53.045 --> 00:18:53.845 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:18:53.845 --> 00:18:56.840 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so I always
shared what I was learning.

00:18:56.840 --> 00:18:58.830 align:middle line:84%
I've always shared what
I was going through.

00:18:58.830 --> 00:19:00.530 align:middle line:90%
I've always-- my books--

00:19:00.530 --> 00:19:04.250 align:middle line:84%
all my books are
very, very honest,

00:19:04.250 --> 00:19:07.488 align:middle line:84%
and they're very brazen in
that way of just sharing,

00:19:07.488 --> 00:19:09.030 align:middle line:84%
oh my god, here is
when I was a mess.

00:19:09.030 --> 00:19:10.537 align:middle line:84%
And when this
wasn't working out.

00:19:10.537 --> 00:19:11.870 align:middle line:90%
It's not your typical self-help.

00:19:11.870 --> 00:19:15.365 align:middle line:84%
Like, "and here's the three
steps I told my clients."

00:19:15.365 --> 00:19:16.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:19:16.580 --> 00:19:17.720 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Because I
believe that people

00:19:17.720 --> 00:19:19.940 align:middle line:84%
learn through authenticity
and through the truth, right?

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:20.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:19:20.740 --> 00:19:22.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: And so I just--

00:19:22.070 --> 00:19:24.440 align:middle line:84%
I always shared
what I was learning,

00:19:24.440 --> 00:19:28.220 align:middle line:84%
and I always shared what
was working for me, and so--

00:19:28.220 --> 00:19:30.890 align:middle line:84%
and I never, ever
planned on this career.

00:19:30.890 --> 00:19:33.050 align:middle line:90%
I never planned on that at all.

00:19:33.050 --> 00:19:35.200 align:middle line:84%
I never thought, gee, I'm
going to be a teacher.

00:19:35.200 --> 00:19:36.980 align:middle line:84%
Or gee, I'm going
to be a seminar

00:19:36.980 --> 00:19:38.360 align:middle line:90%
leader across the country.

00:19:38.360 --> 00:19:40.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to be an
expert-- a national expert.

00:19:40.950 --> 00:19:41.923 align:middle line:90%
I had no plans of that.

00:19:41.923 --> 00:19:43.340 align:middle line:84%
I was just trying
to save my life.

00:19:43.340 --> 00:19:43.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:45.180 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's
all I was doing.

00:19:45.180 --> 00:19:48.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so you dove into
what you thought was best.

00:19:48.570 --> 00:19:49.370 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:19:49.370 --> 00:19:50.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, did you
take writing classes?

00:19:50.930 --> 00:19:51.140 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:19:51.140 --> 00:19:52.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you take
personal development classes?

00:19:52.910 --> 00:19:53.480 align:middle line:90%
What did you take?

00:19:53.480 --> 00:19:55.022 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That is
what saved my life.

00:19:55.022 --> 00:19:56.840 align:middle line:90%
So I just experimented a lot.

00:19:56.840 --> 00:20:00.073 align:middle line:84%
And that's what I always ask
other people to do is, don't--

00:20:00.073 --> 00:20:02.240 align:middle line:84%
everybody wants to immediately
think, OK, that's it.

00:20:02.240 --> 00:20:03.200 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to do x.

00:20:03.200 --> 00:20:04.000 align:middle line:90%
And that's it.

00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.240 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to-- and I want
people to experiment,

00:20:06.240 --> 00:20:08.510 align:middle line:90%
and taste things, and see.

00:20:08.510 --> 00:20:11.150 align:middle line:84%
Because even as a writer,
I didn't know what kind

00:20:11.150 --> 00:20:13.060 align:middle line:90%
of writing I wanted to do.

00:20:13.060 --> 00:20:15.470 align:middle line:84%
Like at first, I thought
I wanted to write poetry.

00:20:15.470 --> 00:20:17.433 align:middle line:84%
And I was so depressed
by that answer.

00:20:17.433 --> 00:20:18.350 align:middle line:90%
I was like, oh my god.

00:20:18.350 --> 00:20:19.560 align:middle line:90%
You've got to be kidding.

00:20:19.560 --> 00:20:20.970 align:middle line:90%
Please give me another answer.

00:20:20.970 --> 00:20:21.750 align:middle line:84%
I don't know if
you ever do that,

00:20:21.750 --> 00:20:23.640 align:middle line:84%
where you're asking your
inner guidance for an answer.

00:20:23.640 --> 00:20:25.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, you get
something and it's like,

00:20:25.390 --> 00:20:26.750 align:middle line:90%
oh, please give me another one.

00:20:26.750 --> 00:20:27.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Was poetry interesting?

00:20:27.380 --> 00:20:28.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Something
that's lucrative.

00:20:28.200 --> 00:20:29.466 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:20:29.466 --> 00:20:30.342 align:middle line:90%


00:20:30.342 --> 00:20:31.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, come on.

00:20:31.220 --> 00:20:32.070 align:middle line:90%
There's some great poetry.

00:20:32.070 --> 00:20:33.170 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: There are
great poets, right?

00:20:33.170 --> 00:20:33.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True. yes.

00:20:33.660 --> 00:20:34.410 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I thought, oh, my god.

00:20:34.410 --> 00:20:36.160 align:middle line:90%
I don't even buy those books.

00:20:36.160 --> 00:20:37.890 align:middle line:90%
Oh, my god.

00:20:37.890 --> 00:20:38.690 align:middle line:90%
But I always--

00:20:38.690 --> 00:20:40.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I think there's like
this slam poetry contests

00:20:40.630 --> 00:20:41.150 align:middle line:90%
and so there's--

00:20:41.150 --> 00:20:41.680 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Sure.

00:20:41.680 --> 00:20:42.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: There's a way.

00:20:42.040 --> 00:20:42.510 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Sure.

00:20:42.510 --> 00:20:43.968 align:middle line:84%
But I always tell
people, you don't

00:20:43.968 --> 00:20:45.450 align:middle line:90%
get to choose what you love.

00:20:45.450 --> 00:20:47.040 align:middle line:84%
You don't get to
choose what you love.

00:20:47.040 --> 00:20:48.160 align:middle line:90%
It chooses you.

00:20:48.160 --> 00:20:48.360 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:20:48.360 --> 00:20:50.610 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: You don't get to
choose your wildest dreams.

00:20:50.610 --> 00:20:51.420 align:middle line:90%
It chooses you.

00:20:51.420 --> 00:20:54.450 align:middle line:84%
You don't get to choose what
lights you up-- what moves you.

00:20:54.450 --> 00:20:56.640 align:middle line:84%
And if you ignore
it and you fight it,

00:20:56.640 --> 00:20:58.590 align:middle line:84%
or you try to water
it down, saying,

00:20:58.590 --> 00:20:59.910 align:middle line:90%
well, I'll make it practical.

00:20:59.910 --> 00:21:00.730 align:middle line:90%
I'll do this.

00:21:00.730 --> 00:21:02.160 align:middle line:90%
I'll do that.

00:21:02.160 --> 00:21:04.740 align:middle line:84%
You will-- I always say, if
you compromise your desire,

00:21:04.740 --> 00:21:06.820 align:middle line:84%
you're going to
compromise your strength.

00:21:06.820 --> 00:21:07.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:21:07.620 --> 00:21:08.210 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:10.252 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But I do think,
though, we get to choose.

00:21:10.252 --> 00:21:12.510 align:middle line:84%
And it may be we-- it
feels the same way.

00:21:12.510 --> 00:21:15.207 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it chooses us and us
choosing with the same energy.

00:21:15.207 --> 00:21:17.040 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I think I
hear what you're saying.

00:21:17.040 --> 00:21:19.360 align:middle line:84%
We get to choose whether
or not we'll listen.

00:21:19.360 --> 00:21:20.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:21:20.160 --> 00:21:21.098 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I get to
choose whether or not

00:21:21.098 --> 00:21:21.230 align:middle line:90%
I'll listen in this lifetime.

00:21:21.230 --> 00:21:23.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Sometimes
it's a good yes.

00:21:23.340 --> 00:21:25.260 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I don't get
to choose what I hear.

00:21:25.260 --> 00:21:25.500 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:21:25.500 --> 00:21:27.292 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I don't get
to choose what it is.

00:21:27.292 --> 00:21:29.760 align:middle line:84%
And very often, your
calling, your dream,

00:21:29.760 --> 00:21:32.940 align:middle line:84%
your next wave of change
might be something

00:21:32.940 --> 00:21:34.890 align:middle line:90%
you don't want to hear.

00:21:34.890 --> 00:21:36.360 align:middle line:90%
I wanted a lucrative answer.

00:21:36.360 --> 00:21:38.310 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to say,
oh, don't do law.

00:21:38.310 --> 00:21:39.160 align:middle line:90%
Be a surgeon.

00:21:39.160 --> 00:21:42.310 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] I wanted
something that--

00:21:42.310 --> 00:21:43.110 align:middle line:90%
that was not my--

00:21:43.110 --> 00:21:44.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You were going to
go through all that again.

00:21:44.550 --> 00:21:45.150 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:21:45.150 --> 00:21:45.865 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I don't think so.

00:21:45.865 --> 00:21:46.665 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:21:46.665 --> 00:21:49.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, let's take
a look here at a video

00:21:49.230 --> 00:21:52.380 align:middle line:84%
that Tama was talking
about when she really goes

00:21:52.380 --> 00:21:54.240 align:middle line:84%
a little bit too
far into the future

00:21:54.240 --> 00:21:57.090 align:middle line:84%
and made some decisions
that wouldn't have maybe

00:21:57.090 --> 00:21:58.050 align:middle line:90%
necessarily served her.

00:21:58.050 --> 00:21:59.040 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:21:59.040 --> 00:21:59.840 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:21:59.840 --> 00:22:02.250 align:middle line:84%
- A lot of us, by the way,
have been successful in life

00:22:02.250 --> 00:22:06.030 align:middle line:84%
because we've known how
to undercut ourselves.

00:22:06.030 --> 00:22:07.920 align:middle line:84%
We've known that--
we've been successful

00:22:07.920 --> 00:22:09.600 align:middle line:84%
because we know how
to clip our wings,

00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:11.970 align:middle line:84%
or be what we think
other people want.

00:22:11.970 --> 00:22:13.830 align:middle line:84%
And then the path
of authenticity,

00:22:13.830 --> 00:22:16.500 align:middle line:84%
the path of really going for
our passion, the path of really

00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:18.510 align:middle line:90%
going out there, is--

00:22:18.510 --> 00:22:22.020 align:middle line:84%
it's that fear of, my
god, we may lose approval.

00:22:22.020 --> 00:22:22.920 align:middle line:90%
But here's the thing.

00:22:22.920 --> 00:22:25.850 align:middle line:84%
You may lose other
people, but it's worth it,

00:22:25.850 --> 00:22:28.640 align:middle line:84%
because I don't want
you to lose yourself.

00:22:28.640 --> 00:22:32.790 align:middle line:84%
Because you lose yourself, you
lose everyone and everything.

00:22:32.790 --> 00:22:35.970 align:middle line:84%
I remember years ago,
I was really scared

00:22:35.970 --> 00:22:39.870 align:middle line:84%
of what my father would
say when I left law.

00:22:39.870 --> 00:22:42.120 align:middle line:84%
I always joke about my mother,
but I was really scared

00:22:42.120 --> 00:22:45.110 align:middle line:84%
about my father, because
he was really volatile.

00:22:45.110 --> 00:22:48.450 align:middle line:84%
And I thought he
would excommunicate me

00:22:48.450 --> 00:22:49.260 align:middle line:90%
from the family.

00:22:49.260 --> 00:22:50.420 align:middle line:90%
I really did, because he was--

00:22:50.420 --> 00:22:51.337 align:middle line:90%
he could be like that.

00:22:51.337 --> 00:22:53.472 align:middle line:90%
He was really a volatile guy.

00:22:53.472 --> 00:22:54.930 align:middle line:84%
And I was terrified,
and I remember

00:22:54.930 --> 00:22:57.980 align:middle line:84%
telling a therapist at the time,
I don't want to lose his love.

00:22:57.980 --> 00:22:58.780 align:middle line:90%
I'm scared.

00:22:58.780 --> 00:22:59.560 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to do this.

00:22:59.560 --> 00:23:00.440 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to lose my father.

00:23:00.440 --> 00:23:01.690 align:middle line:90%
I don't want to lose his love.

00:23:01.690 --> 00:23:04.920 align:middle line:84%
And she just said, if
you could lose somebody

00:23:04.920 --> 00:23:08.150 align:middle line:84%
by being who you are, then
you don't have their love.

00:23:08.150 --> 00:23:09.130 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:23:09.130 --> 00:23:10.680 align:middle line:90%


00:23:10.680 --> 00:23:12.680 align:middle line:84%
If you could lose somebody
by being who you are,

00:23:12.680 --> 00:23:13.972 align:middle line:90%
then you don't have their love.

00:23:13.972 --> 00:23:15.450 align:middle line:84%
And then years
later, I discovered

00:23:15.450 --> 00:23:18.240 align:middle line:84%
"A Course in Miracles,"
which I teach and I love.

00:23:18.240 --> 00:23:22.500 align:middle line:84%
And "A Course of Miracles" says,
nothing real can be threatened.

00:23:22.500 --> 00:23:24.390 align:middle line:90%
Nothing real can be threatened.

00:23:24.390 --> 00:23:26.230 align:middle line:84%
By the way, I did
tell my father.

00:23:26.230 --> 00:23:27.330 align:middle line:90%
I was so scared.

00:23:27.330 --> 00:23:28.620 align:middle line:90%
I prepared.

00:23:28.620 --> 00:23:30.540 align:middle line:84%
I went to god knows how
many therapy sessions.

00:23:30.540 --> 00:23:31.560 align:middle line:90%
God knows, right?

00:23:31.560 --> 00:23:33.638 align:middle line:84%
I told my father and
he just went, eh.

00:23:33.638 --> 00:23:34.438 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:23:34.438 --> 00:23:35.238 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:35.238 --> 00:23:37.870 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, I spent
thousands of dollars--

00:23:37.870 --> 00:23:39.316 align:middle line:90%
[HYPERVENTILATING]

00:23:39.316 --> 00:23:43.682 align:middle line:90%


00:23:43.682 --> 00:23:45.630 align:middle line:90%
I was like, what?

00:23:45.630 --> 00:23:49.770 align:middle line:84%
I have killed so many trees
on this issue journaling.

00:23:49.770 --> 00:23:51.470 align:middle line:90%
And he was just like, yeah.

00:23:51.470 --> 00:23:52.270 align:middle line:90%
You're smart.

00:23:52.270 --> 00:23:53.226 align:middle line:90%
You'll figure it out, I know.

00:23:53.226 --> 00:23:53.960 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:53.960 --> 00:23:54.600 align:middle line:90%
What?

00:23:54.600 --> 00:23:55.892 align:middle line:90%
What, you got something to eat?

00:23:55.892 --> 00:23:57.420 align:middle line:90%
It was like-- so anyway.

00:23:57.420 --> 00:24:01.410 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] It's just amazing, so--

00:24:01.410 --> 00:24:04.595 align:middle line:84%
but by the way, I never
felt so loved in my life.

00:24:04.595 --> 00:24:05.970 align:middle line:84%
I never felt so
loved in my life,

00:24:05.970 --> 00:24:07.800 align:middle line:84%
because he didn't
excommunicate me.

00:24:07.800 --> 00:24:11.380 align:middle line:84%
And that was probably his way
of saying, I love you madly.

00:24:11.380 --> 00:24:12.180 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:24:12.180 --> 00:24:12.570 align:middle line:90%
Like, meh.

00:24:12.570 --> 00:24:13.420 align:middle line:90%
Eh.

00:24:13.420 --> 00:24:14.270 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:24:14.270 --> 00:24:16.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That wasn't the
reaction you expected.

00:24:16.470 --> 00:24:18.560 align:middle line:90%
How did you feel?

00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:22.340 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I just felt so loved.

00:24:22.340 --> 00:24:25.490 align:middle line:10%
I just was amazed, because--

00:24:25.490 --> 00:24:27.470 align:middle line:10%
and I think that's
the amazing thing,

00:24:27.470 --> 00:24:31.130 align:middle line:10%
is that when you make these
life changes in your own life,

00:24:31.130 --> 00:24:34.700 align:middle line:10%
you get to really see
your real relationships.

00:24:34.700 --> 00:24:36.590 align:middle line:84%
If you're being
the real you, you

00:24:36.590 --> 00:24:39.470 align:middle line:84%
get to meet the real
self of other people.

00:24:39.470 --> 00:24:42.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think you get even
more intimacy with people,

00:24:42.620 --> 00:24:45.430 align:middle line:84%
and/or you find out
who aren't your people.

00:24:45.430 --> 00:24:47.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, these stories,
though, also we tell ourselves,

00:24:47.930 --> 00:24:51.767 align:middle line:84%
that we think and we project
and we future pace ourselves

00:24:51.767 --> 00:24:54.350 align:middle line:84%
and thinking all this stuff is
going to happen, and it hasn't.

00:24:54.350 --> 00:24:55.100 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:24:55.100 --> 00:24:55.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And I--

00:24:55.590 --> 00:24:58.100 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And I have a really
great story about that,

00:24:58.100 --> 00:24:59.635 align:middle line:90%
of it's just--

00:24:59.635 --> 00:25:01.010 align:middle line:84%
I always tell my
clients that you

00:25:01.010 --> 00:25:03.197 align:middle line:90%
can't plan an inspired life.

00:25:03.197 --> 00:25:04.280 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's in their head.

00:25:04.280 --> 00:25:05.727 align:middle line:84%
They're trying to
plan everything.

00:25:05.727 --> 00:25:07.060 align:middle line:90%
They're trying to figure it out.

00:25:07.060 --> 00:25:08.580 align:middle line:84%
How do I get to
A to B to C to D?

00:25:08.580 --> 00:25:09.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:25:09.380 --> 00:25:11.270 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And my
greatest story about how

00:25:11.270 --> 00:25:13.430 align:middle line:84%
I got my book
published was again,

00:25:13.430 --> 00:25:15.640 align:middle line:84%
like you said, about
following that next step

00:25:15.640 --> 00:25:16.440 align:middle line:90%
and that next step.

00:25:16.440 --> 00:25:17.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The breadcrumbs.

00:25:17.080 --> 00:25:17.720 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: With the breadcrumbs.

00:25:17.720 --> 00:25:17.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:25:17.820 --> 00:25:19.190 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so when
I finally finished

00:25:19.190 --> 00:25:20.990 align:middle line:84%
writing my first
book-- it took me 12

00:25:20.990 --> 00:25:22.310 align:middle line:90%
years to write my first book.

00:25:22.310 --> 00:25:23.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:25:23.110 --> 00:25:24.403 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS] And--

00:25:24.403 --> 00:25:25.820 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Good to
know, for authors.

00:25:25.820 --> 00:25:26.150 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I know.

00:25:26.150 --> 00:25:27.858 align:middle line:84%
I always tell people,
it took me 11 years

00:25:27.858 --> 00:25:29.835 align:middle line:84%
to heal, and 11 years
to believe in myself,

00:25:29.835 --> 00:25:32.210 align:middle line:84%
and 11 years to learn this,
and one year to write a book.

00:25:32.210 --> 00:25:33.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:25:33.010 --> 00:25:34.880 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So-- but
anyways, I didn't

00:25:34.880 --> 00:25:36.320 align:middle line:90%
know how to get it published.

00:25:36.320 --> 00:25:36.850 align:middle line:90%
I didn't know.

00:25:36.850 --> 00:25:37.550 align:middle line:90%
What do you do?

00:25:37.550 --> 00:25:38.810 align:middle line:84%
How do you get it out
there in the world?

00:25:38.810 --> 00:25:40.910 align:middle line:84%
And so I read about self
publishing and commercial

00:25:40.910 --> 00:25:41.710 align:middle line:90%
publishing.

00:25:41.710 --> 00:25:44.000 align:middle line:84%
And I kept hearing
an inner voice.

00:25:44.000 --> 00:25:47.210 align:middle line:84%
And it just kept saying,
just put it in the river.

00:25:47.210 --> 00:25:49.010 align:middle line:90%
Just put it in the river.

00:25:49.010 --> 00:25:50.300 align:middle line:90%
Which makes no sense.

00:25:50.300 --> 00:25:50.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:25:50.670 --> 00:25:51.840 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: It's--
[LAUGHS] it was like,

00:25:51.840 --> 00:25:52.923 align:middle line:90%
what kind of plan is that?

00:25:52.923 --> 00:25:54.590 align:middle line:90%
Please give me something linear.

00:25:54.590 --> 00:25:56.720 align:middle line:84%
But it was this guidance,
and I knew what it meant.

00:25:56.720 --> 00:25:59.480 align:middle line:84%
It meant, get it out
there some way, somehow.

00:25:59.480 --> 00:26:00.890 align:middle line:90%
Self-publish it if you have to.

00:26:00.890 --> 00:26:02.780 align:middle line:84%
Put your own money
into it if you have to.

00:26:02.780 --> 00:26:04.370 align:middle line:84%
Just get it into
the stream of life.

00:26:04.370 --> 00:26:06.350 align:middle line:84%
If it's supposed to
go somewhere, it will.

00:26:06.350 --> 00:26:08.090 align:middle line:84%
But you know how, like I
was saying before, you get

00:26:08.090 --> 00:26:09.200 align:middle line:90%
answers you don't want to hear?

00:26:09.200 --> 00:26:10.867 align:middle line:84%
It's like, oh, I don't
want that answer.

00:26:10.867 --> 00:26:14.000 align:middle line:84%
I want to-- but
anyways I ended up

00:26:14.000 --> 00:26:16.550 align:middle line:84%
having the guts to finally
self-publish my first book

00:26:16.550 --> 00:26:19.160 align:middle line:90%
after all of this.

00:26:19.160 --> 00:26:21.230 align:middle line:84%
And it started spreading
through word of mouth.

00:26:21.230 --> 00:26:22.960 align:middle line:84%
It hit "The Denver
Post" bestseller list.

00:26:22.960 --> 00:26:24.800 align:middle line:84%
It hit "The Business"
bestseller list.

00:26:24.800 --> 00:26:27.620 align:middle line:84%
And then four months
after I self-published,

00:26:27.620 --> 00:26:31.520 align:middle line:84%
I got an email from a woman
who worked for Random House.

00:26:31.520 --> 00:26:34.190 align:middle line:84%
She was in marketing and
publicity as a vice president.

00:26:34.190 --> 00:26:36.050 align:middle line:84%
And she was in a
career transition,

00:26:36.050 --> 00:26:38.150 align:middle line:84%
and she had somehow found
my self-published book

00:26:38.150 --> 00:26:40.340 align:middle line:90%
on the internet.

00:26:40.340 --> 00:26:43.400 align:middle line:84%
And she wrote, "Your fairy
godmother has arrived."

00:26:43.400 --> 00:26:45.250 align:middle line:84%
Your fairy godmother--
that's the email.

00:26:45.250 --> 00:26:46.050 align:middle line:90%
I got it.

00:26:46.050 --> 00:26:47.150 align:middle line:84%
And she wrote to
me and said it was

00:26:47.150 --> 00:26:48.860 align:middle line:84%
the best book she'd
ever read on finding

00:26:48.860 --> 00:26:50.027 align:middle line:90%
your calling and your dream.

00:26:50.027 --> 00:26:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And I want to get it published
by a New York publisher.

00:26:52.510 --> 00:26:55.730 align:middle line:84%
And so it was this amazing,
amazing thing about,

00:26:55.730 --> 00:26:56.840 align:middle line:90%
you can't plan that.

00:26:56.840 --> 00:26:59.930 align:middle line:84%
How can you plan that I'm
going to have a meltdown for 12

00:26:59.930 --> 00:27:01.215 align:middle line:90%
years writing this book?

00:27:01.215 --> 00:27:02.840 align:middle line:84%
Some other woman at
the end of 12 years

00:27:02.840 --> 00:27:04.850 align:middle line:84%
is going to have a
meltdown in her own career.

00:27:04.850 --> 00:27:06.020 align:middle line:90%
She's going to find it.

00:27:06.020 --> 00:27:08.220 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I'm going
to go to my next level.

00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:12.230 align:middle line:84%
But I deeply know that everybody
has something extraordinary

00:27:12.230 --> 00:27:15.878 align:middle line:84%
in them, and if they follow that
breadcrumb moment by moment,

00:27:15.878 --> 00:27:18.170 align:middle line:84%
they're going to get to
someplace they could never have

00:27:18.170 --> 00:27:19.823 align:middle line:90%
gotten in a conventional way.

00:27:19.823 --> 00:27:21.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You seem to
receive a lot of guidance.

00:27:21.740 --> 00:27:24.800 align:middle line:84%
Do you have a practice
through meditation, or--

00:27:24.800 --> 00:27:25.827 align:middle line:90%
what is your practice?

00:27:25.827 --> 00:27:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I receive
a lot of guidance,

00:27:27.410 --> 00:27:28.550 align:middle line:90%
because I have a lot of fear.

00:27:28.550 --> 00:27:29.190 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:27:29.190 --> 00:27:29.650 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So you're always active.

00:27:29.650 --> 00:27:31.307 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I have a
very active mind.

00:27:31.307 --> 00:27:33.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I would never have
been able to tell that.

00:27:33.390 --> 00:27:34.280 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: No, I'm
sure you couldn't.

00:27:34.280 --> 00:27:36.050 align:middle line:90%
I'm sure I hide it really well.

00:27:36.050 --> 00:27:38.370 align:middle line:84%
It takes a team to
manage this brain.

00:27:38.370 --> 00:27:39.352 align:middle line:90%
Let's put it that way.

00:27:39.352 --> 00:27:40.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I can see that.

00:27:40.310 --> 00:27:41.360 align:middle line:90%
You have a lot of energy.

00:27:41.360 --> 00:27:42.180 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I have
a lot of energy.

00:27:42.180 --> 00:27:42.400 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:27:42.400 --> 00:27:43.817 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And if
this energy isn't

00:27:43.817 --> 00:27:46.610 align:middle line:84%
directed towards something
positive and useful,

00:27:46.610 --> 00:27:47.478 align:middle line:90%
it's not good.

00:27:47.478 --> 00:27:48.770 align:middle line:90%
And that's what I teach people.

00:27:48.770 --> 00:27:50.145 align:middle line:84%
You can use your
mind either way.

00:27:50.145 --> 00:27:52.080 align:middle line:84%
So to answer your
question about my--

00:27:52.080 --> 00:27:52.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Guidance.

00:27:52.880 --> 00:27:54.800 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: --practice
and guidance,

00:27:54.800 --> 00:27:56.360 align:middle line:84%
I've taught "A
Course in Miracles"

00:27:56.360 --> 00:28:00.830 align:middle line:84%
for close to 30 years,
and so that's my path.

00:28:00.830 --> 00:28:02.900 align:middle line:84%
And I've never been
a great meditator.

00:28:02.900 --> 00:28:04.940 align:middle line:90%
I want to say, oh, yes, I am.

00:28:04.940 --> 00:28:05.940 align:middle line:90%
But I journal a lot.

00:28:05.940 --> 00:28:06.740 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:28:06.740 --> 00:28:07.040 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: That's--

00:28:07.040 --> 00:28:08.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: For people
that aren't familiar,

00:28:08.340 --> 00:28:09.860 align:middle line:90%
what is "A Course in Miracles"?

00:28:09.860 --> 00:28:12.410 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: "A Course in Miracles"
is a spiritual psychotherapy

00:28:12.410 --> 00:28:16.640 align:middle line:84%
program that teaches you how to
live in love instead of fear.

00:28:16.640 --> 00:28:19.160 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a mind training
program that really--

00:28:19.160 --> 00:28:21.740 align:middle line:84%
and again, because I
have such an active mind,

00:28:21.740 --> 00:28:23.700 align:middle line:84%
it worked for me
of that, it really

00:28:23.700 --> 00:28:26.720 align:middle line:84%
directs the right
use of your mind.

00:28:26.720 --> 00:28:29.163 align:middle line:84%
That at any minute, you could
be having a fearful thought,

00:28:29.163 --> 00:28:30.830 align:middle line:84%
or you could be having
a loving thought.

00:28:30.830 --> 00:28:31.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:28:31.630 --> 00:28:33.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so it's
a practice, like--

00:28:33.650 --> 00:28:35.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Of training towards
the loving thoughts?

00:28:35.060 --> 00:28:35.375 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Exactly.

00:28:35.375 --> 00:28:36.175 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:28:36.175 --> 00:28:37.010 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Exactly.

00:28:37.010 --> 00:28:39.320 align:middle line:84%
And with all of this stuff
that we're talking about,

00:28:39.320 --> 00:28:41.750 align:middle line:84%
like even when you said
about failure, it's like,

00:28:41.750 --> 00:28:44.390 align:middle line:84%
this is a practice
every single day.

00:28:44.390 --> 00:28:45.560 align:middle line:90%
People, I think again--

00:28:45.560 --> 00:28:47.060 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the
things I want people

00:28:47.060 --> 00:28:49.338 align:middle line:84%
to know in all of my work
is that people think I'm

00:28:49.338 --> 00:28:50.630 align:middle line:90%
going to beat that seven steps.

00:28:50.630 --> 00:28:53.277 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to hire that
perfect coach, and that's it.

00:28:53.277 --> 00:28:55.110 align:middle line:84%
I will never have to
deal with change again.

00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:56.840 align:middle line:84%
I will never have to
deal with my mind again.

00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:57.470 align:middle line:90%
Good luck.

00:28:57.470 --> 00:28:58.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:28:58.270 --> 00:28:59.540 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Good luck on that.

00:28:59.540 --> 00:29:00.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, you
write about something

00:29:00.470 --> 00:29:01.890 align:middle line:90%
called inspired self-dialogues.

00:29:01.890 --> 00:29:02.690 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:29:02.690 --> 00:29:03.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What are they?

00:29:03.380 --> 00:29:04.180 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:29:04.180 --> 00:29:07.820 align:middle line:84%
So it's a technique that is in
"Thriving Through Uncertainty,"

00:29:07.820 --> 00:29:09.000 align:middle line:90%
and it's also on my website.

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:10.940 align:middle line:84%
It's a technique I
use almost every day.

00:29:10.940 --> 00:29:12.470 align:middle line:90%
It's amazing for me.

00:29:12.470 --> 00:29:14.840 align:middle line:84%
It's a journaling technique,
and what it is is,

00:29:14.840 --> 00:29:16.910 align:middle line:90%
when your mind is crazy--

00:29:16.910 --> 00:29:19.790 align:middle line:84%
I could never shut it up
in meditation long enough

00:29:19.790 --> 00:29:20.630 align:middle line:90%
to get an answer.

00:29:20.630 --> 00:29:21.370 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The monkey mind.

00:29:21.370 --> 00:29:21.620 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:29:21.620 --> 00:29:22.420 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:29:22.420 --> 00:29:25.390 align:middle line:84%
And so in the inspired
self-dialogue,

00:29:25.390 --> 00:29:26.450 align:middle line:90%
I'll write for my fear.

00:29:26.450 --> 00:29:27.740 align:middle line:90%
I'll write when I'm crazy.

00:29:27.740 --> 00:29:29.098 align:middle line:90%
Like, I'm scared.

00:29:29.098 --> 00:29:30.140 align:middle line:90%
The check didn't come in.

00:29:30.140 --> 00:29:31.490 align:middle line:90%
I'm not going to make money.

00:29:31.490 --> 00:29:32.760 align:middle line:90%
Whatever the fear de jure is.

00:29:32.760 --> 00:29:33.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:36.590 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so--
and then I write back

00:29:36.590 --> 00:29:38.780 align:middle line:84%
from this incredibly
loving voice.

00:29:38.780 --> 00:29:41.090 align:middle line:84%
The most loving presence
I could possibly

00:29:41.090 --> 00:29:43.070 align:middle line:84%
ever imagine-- the
voice of your spirit,

00:29:43.070 --> 00:29:44.850 align:middle line:90%
the voice of your genius.

00:29:44.850 --> 00:29:48.110 align:middle line:10%
Some people find it helpful to
think in terms of, what would

00:29:48.110 --> 00:29:52.070 align:middle line:10%
you say to your best
friend or to your child?

00:29:52.070 --> 00:29:56.630 align:middle line:84%
If your child or your best
friend was in pain or anxiety,

00:29:56.630 --> 00:29:58.970 align:middle line:84%
you would say something
loving and strong.

00:29:58.970 --> 00:30:01.107 align:middle line:84%
And so I write back
from that voice.

00:30:01.107 --> 00:30:03.440 align:middle line:84%
And then it's a conversation,
because sometimes my voice

00:30:03.440 --> 00:30:05.600 align:middle line:90%
will say, relax, dear one.

00:30:05.600 --> 00:30:06.530 align:middle line:90%
It's fine.

00:30:06.530 --> 00:30:08.030 align:middle line:84%
Blah, blah, blah--
whatever it's going to say.

00:30:08.030 --> 00:30:09.360 align:middle line:84%
And I'll be like,
I am not relaxed.

00:30:09.360 --> 00:30:10.450 align:middle line:90%
I'd better be a child of light.

00:30:10.450 --> 00:30:11.330 align:middle line:84%
They're going to
turn the lights off.

00:30:11.330 --> 00:30:12.300 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:30:12.300 --> 00:30:16.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS] Well,
doesn't that make you bipolar?

00:30:16.230 --> 00:30:18.272 align:middle line:84%
You're sitting here
saying I'm freaking out.

00:30:18.272 --> 00:30:19.230 align:middle line:90%
And you're like, relax.

00:30:19.230 --> 00:30:19.510 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Relax.

00:30:19.510 --> 00:30:19.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Be calm.

00:30:19.940 --> 00:30:20.760 align:middle line:90%
All the--

00:30:20.760 --> 00:30:21.500 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I love that.

00:30:21.500 --> 00:30:22.375 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Is that true?

00:30:22.375 --> 00:30:25.580 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So I love
that you said that.

00:30:25.580 --> 00:30:29.630 align:middle line:84%
What I think it is is that we
have both voices in our mind.

00:30:29.630 --> 00:30:32.960 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is that
the fear and anxiety blocks

00:30:32.960 --> 00:30:34.760 align:middle line:90%
your highest intelligence.

00:30:34.760 --> 00:30:37.490 align:middle line:84%
The fear and anxiety
blo-- even medical science

00:30:37.490 --> 00:30:39.920 align:middle line:84%
says that it restricts
your blood chemistry.

00:30:39.920 --> 00:30:42.110 align:middle line:84%
It just-- it restricts
your thought flow.

00:30:42.110 --> 00:30:44.270 align:middle line:84%
And so when you're scared
and you're amped up,

00:30:44.270 --> 00:30:46.850 align:middle line:84%
you don't have access
to your resourceful

00:30:46.850 --> 00:30:48.840 align:middle line:90%
mind-- your creative ideas.

00:30:48.840 --> 00:30:50.827 align:middle line:84%
And so we do have two
voices in our mind.

00:30:50.827 --> 00:30:52.660 align:middle line:84%
And what I'm always
trying to teach people--

00:30:52.660 --> 00:30:52.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: True.

00:30:52.790 --> 00:30:53.590 align:middle line:90%
More than that.

00:30:53.590 --> 00:30:54.800 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah, at least.

00:30:54.800 --> 00:30:56.480 align:middle line:84%
What I'm always
trying to teach people

00:30:56.480 --> 00:30:59.960 align:middle line:84%
is that you have a higher
intelligence and a love that

00:30:59.960 --> 00:31:02.870 align:middle line:84%
can guide you through
anything, if you listen to it.

00:31:02.870 --> 00:31:04.370 align:middle line:84%
But you are listening
to that fear.

00:31:04.370 --> 00:31:05.600 align:middle line:90%
You're indulging that fear.

00:31:05.600 --> 00:31:07.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're giving
in the opportunity

00:31:07.520 --> 00:31:10.750 align:middle line:84%
to hear another voice,
to have another opinion.

00:31:10.750 --> 00:31:13.010 align:middle line:84%
And I like the
idea that you give

00:31:13.010 --> 00:31:15.270 align:middle line:84%
the best advice you possibly
could to a best friend.

00:31:15.270 --> 00:31:16.070 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:31:16.070 --> 00:31:17.682 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or a child,
or a loved one.

00:31:17.682 --> 00:31:19.640 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Because you
speak differently to them

00:31:19.640 --> 00:31:20.720 align:middle line:90%
than you do to yourself.

00:31:20.720 --> 00:31:21.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:31:21.350 --> 00:31:22.267 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Why is that?

00:31:22.267 --> 00:31:23.955 align:middle line:84%
My best friend--
oh, you can do it.

00:31:23.955 --> 00:31:24.830 align:middle line:90%
You can do it, honey.

00:31:24.830 --> 00:31:25.820 align:middle line:90%
I believe in you.

00:31:25.820 --> 00:31:26.680 align:middle line:90%
Me, not so much.

00:31:26.680 --> 00:31:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, there's
also people, though,

00:31:28.430 --> 00:31:30.770 align:middle line:84%
in your life that will
have other voices as well,

00:31:30.770 --> 00:31:32.780 align:middle line:90%
talking about other voices.

00:31:32.780 --> 00:31:34.280 align:middle line:84%
Where you hear
them in your head--

00:31:34.280 --> 00:31:36.100 align:middle line:84%
the voice of your mother
and the voice of--

00:31:36.100 --> 00:31:36.440 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:31:36.440 --> 00:31:36.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Actually, we have a--

00:31:36.980 --> 00:31:37.600 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's
what therapy if for.

00:31:37.600 --> 00:31:37.750 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:31:37.750 --> 00:31:38.562 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:31:38.562 --> 00:31:39.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The voice
of your therapist.

00:31:39.780 --> 00:31:39.910 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES:

00:31:39.910 --> 00:31:40.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:31:40.040 --> 00:31:41.165 align:middle line:90%
Everybody gives you advice.

00:31:41.165 --> 00:31:41.965 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:31:41.965 --> 00:31:44.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do you know
what's the right advice?

00:31:44.060 --> 00:31:44.860 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm.

00:31:44.860 --> 00:31:46.550 align:middle line:90%
That's a great question.

00:31:46.550 --> 00:31:49.580 align:middle line:84%
I think-- so I have a chapter in
"Thriving Through Uncertainty"

00:31:49.580 --> 00:31:52.010 align:middle line:84%
that says, think twice
before you take advice.

00:31:52.010 --> 00:31:53.510 align:middle line:84%
Think twice before
you take advice.

00:31:53.510 --> 00:31:53.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:31:53.720 --> 00:31:56.053 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Because everybody's
coming at you with advice.

00:31:56.053 --> 00:31:58.010 align:middle line:84%
And especially if
you're shifting careers

00:31:58.010 --> 00:31:59.510 align:middle line:84%
or you're an
entrepreneur and you're

00:31:59.510 --> 00:32:00.885 align:middle line:84%
doing the life of
your dreams and

00:32:00.885 --> 00:32:03.710 align:middle line:84%
you get all this even business
advice and internet advice.

00:32:03.710 --> 00:32:07.620 align:middle line:84%
The main thing I would say is,
notice how it feels to you.

00:32:07.620 --> 00:32:09.410 align:middle line:84%
How do you feel when
you hear that advice?

00:32:09.410 --> 00:32:13.340 align:middle line:84%
If that advice makes you feel
peaceful or hopeful or excited,

00:32:13.340 --> 00:32:14.450 align:middle line:90%
I'd listen to it.

00:32:14.450 --> 00:32:15.740 align:middle line:90%
If not, I wouldn't.

00:32:15.740 --> 00:32:18.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think the main
thing I want you to do

00:32:18.020 --> 00:32:20.210 align:middle line:90%
is to start listening to your--

00:32:20.210 --> 00:32:22.670 align:middle line:84%
I want you to listen to people,
but then filter it through.

00:32:22.670 --> 00:32:25.130 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, take for example
something like Facebook.

00:32:25.130 --> 00:32:25.370 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:32:25.370 --> 00:32:26.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It changes all the time.

00:32:26.800 --> 00:32:28.640 align:middle line:84%
They're constantly
making it better, and--

00:32:28.640 --> 00:32:28.970 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:32:28.970 --> 00:32:30.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]
It's very confuse--

00:32:30.560 --> 00:32:32.530 align:middle line:84%
and you're listening
to this idea and that.

00:32:32.530 --> 00:32:35.180 align:middle line:84%
Maybe you should post
this way and do that.

00:32:35.180 --> 00:32:39.410 align:middle line:84%
How do you really filter
through all the noise?

00:32:39.410 --> 00:32:42.230 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I think that is the
biggest thing we have to do.

00:32:42.230 --> 00:32:44.605 align:middle line:84%
I think that is the most
important thing we have to do.

00:32:44.605 --> 00:32:45.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Filter
through the noise?

00:32:45.980 --> 00:32:47.930 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Filter through
the noise, or stop

00:32:47.930 --> 00:32:49.770 align:middle line:90%
listening to external advice.

00:32:49.770 --> 00:32:50.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm.

00:32:50.570 --> 00:32:52.910 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Stop listening to
external advice, because we

00:32:52.910 --> 00:32:54.410 align:middle line:90%
think the experts know.

00:32:54.410 --> 00:32:58.880 align:middle line:84%
And I want you on an original
path that no one has--

00:32:58.880 --> 00:33:00.072 align:middle line:90%
no one knows your path.

00:33:00.072 --> 00:33:01.280 align:middle line:90%
You haven't been here before.

00:33:01.280 --> 00:33:04.070 align:middle line:84%
There's genius in you
that we don't know yet.

00:33:04.070 --> 00:33:07.520 align:middle line:84%
I spent so much time when I--
when my second book came out,

00:33:07.520 --> 00:33:10.058 align:middle line:84%
"Inspired and Unstoppable,"
worrying about, oh, Facebook.

00:33:10.058 --> 00:33:12.350 align:middle line:84%
And you should do this, and
you should do social media,

00:33:12.350 --> 00:33:13.070 align:middle line:90%
and I should do that.

00:33:13.070 --> 00:33:14.780 align:middle line:84%
I'm not doing this,
and I have to block.

00:33:14.780 --> 00:33:16.130 align:middle line:90%
But wait, I have to do this.

00:33:16.130 --> 00:33:20.990 align:middle line:84%
And I was making myself crazy,
instead of really following,

00:33:20.990 --> 00:33:22.590 align:middle line:90%
what do you want to do, Tam?

00:33:22.590 --> 00:33:24.540 align:middle line:90%
I'm a speaker.

00:33:24.540 --> 00:33:25.340 align:middle line:90%
I'm a speaker.

00:33:25.340 --> 00:33:26.140 align:middle line:90%
I'm a writer.

00:33:26.140 --> 00:33:27.240 align:middle line:90%
That's where I belong.

00:33:27.240 --> 00:33:29.360 align:middle line:84%
I didn't belong doing
every single thing.

00:33:29.360 --> 00:33:29.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:33:29.690 --> 00:33:31.670 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And you're trying to
do everything right, instead

00:33:31.670 --> 00:33:32.870 align:middle line:90%
of what's right for you.

00:33:32.870 --> 00:33:34.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And sometimes it
really does take focus,

00:33:34.520 --> 00:33:36.770 align:middle line:84%
and the people that really
do that on a marketing level

00:33:36.770 --> 00:33:37.520 align:middle line:90%
are brilliant at it.

00:33:37.520 --> 00:33:38.270 align:middle line:90%
That's their genius.

00:33:38.270 --> 00:33:38.720 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:33:38.720 --> 00:33:39.940 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And let them do that.

00:33:39.940 --> 00:33:40.095 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:33:40.095 --> 00:33:40.970 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah, that.

00:33:40.970 --> 00:33:44.240 align:middle line:84%
And also that again, there's
this belief system that there's

00:33:44.240 --> 00:33:45.710 align:middle line:90%
a right way to do it.

00:33:45.710 --> 00:33:49.610 align:middle line:84%
I got a book published
in a way that everybody

00:33:49.610 --> 00:33:50.832 align:middle line:90%
told me was crazy.

00:33:50.832 --> 00:33:52.790 align:middle line:84%
Everybody told me, you
can't just write a book.

00:33:52.790 --> 00:33:53.480 align:middle line:90%
You can't just write it.

00:33:53.480 --> 00:33:53.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Self-published.

00:33:53.830 --> 00:33:54.670 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: You can't say,
oh, it's self-published

00:33:54.670 --> 00:33:56.670 align:middle line:84%
and think it's going to
go somewhere-- whatever.

00:33:56.670 --> 00:33:59.095 align:middle line:84%
And I kept following
that inner voice.

00:33:59.095 --> 00:34:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes your
inner voice is

00:34:00.470 --> 00:34:04.520 align:middle line:84%
going to tell you something
different or alternative that

00:34:04.520 --> 00:34:06.440 align:middle line:90%
is not what the experts say.

00:34:06.440 --> 00:34:08.540 align:middle line:84%
But again, I deeply
believe that we're here

00:34:08.540 --> 00:34:10.440 align:middle line:90%
to be new answers in the world.

00:34:10.440 --> 00:34:12.110 align:middle line:84%
We're not here to
fit into the world.

00:34:12.110 --> 00:34:13.610 align:middle line:90%
We're here to reshape the world.

00:34:13.610 --> 00:34:16.010 align:middle line:84%
We're here to make it
new with our answers,

00:34:16.010 --> 00:34:18.260 align:middle line:84%
and that's going to come
from listening to our genius.

00:34:18.260 --> 00:34:19.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:34:19.550 --> 00:34:22.781 align:middle line:84%
Well, let's take a look here at
Tama talking about what she did

00:34:22.781 --> 00:34:23.989 align:middle line:90%
when things got really tough.

00:34:23.989 --> 00:34:24.789 align:middle line:90%
Take a look.

00:34:24.789 --> 00:34:26.020 align:middle line:90%
