00:34:26.020 --> 00:34:30.750 align:middle line:10%
- I guess I wanted to start by
just asking a question to you.

00:34:30.750 --> 00:34:37.210 align:middle line:10%
Is it me, or has life
ratcheted up a notch?

00:34:37.210 --> 00:34:39.639 align:middle line:90%
Or two or three, yeah.

00:34:39.639 --> 00:34:41.830 align:middle line:84%
It's like, everyone
you know is going

00:34:41.830 --> 00:34:43.690 align:middle line:84%
through some kind
of uncertainty,

00:34:43.690 --> 00:34:46.360 align:middle line:90%
or some kind of difficulty.

00:34:46.360 --> 00:34:47.560 align:middle line:90%
or some kind of challenge.

00:34:47.560 --> 00:34:50.300 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe you're in
some kind of change.

00:34:50.300 --> 00:34:53.830 align:middle line:10%
And I think it's as though
the universe is saying,

00:34:53.830 --> 00:34:57.550 align:middle line:10%
the grace period is now over.

00:34:57.550 --> 00:34:59.140 align:middle line:10%
The grace period is now over.

00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:00.850 align:middle line:10%
We've been studying this stuff.

00:35:00.850 --> 00:35:02.500 align:middle line:10%
We know this stuff.

00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:04.570 align:middle line:10%
You know you have
an inner voice.

00:35:04.570 --> 00:35:06.970 align:middle line:10%
You know you have
this love inside you.

00:35:06.970 --> 00:35:10.060 align:middle line:10%
Some of us know that there
is this power within us

00:35:10.060 --> 00:35:11.590 align:middle line:10%
that we can believe
in, that we can

00:35:11.590 --> 00:35:13.900 align:middle line:10%
tap at any single time in our--

00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:15.490 align:middle line:10%
at any time.

00:35:15.490 --> 00:35:17.590 align:middle line:90%
And it's time to do that.

00:35:17.590 --> 00:35:20.680 align:middle line:84%
Because I think for me, one
of the things I'm learning

00:35:20.680 --> 00:35:25.180 align:middle line:84%
is it's time to get out
of your head and be led.

00:35:25.180 --> 00:35:27.410 align:middle line:84%
It's time to get out of
your head and be led.

00:35:27.410 --> 00:35:27.710 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:35:27.710 --> 00:35:28.510 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:35:28.510 --> 00:35:31.870 align:middle line:84%
It's time to-- because
if you feel as though--

00:35:31.870 --> 00:35:34.900 align:middle line:84%
but you're scared, or you
don't know what's going on,

00:35:34.900 --> 00:35:37.870 align:middle line:84%
or what's supposed to
happen, or there's change,

00:35:37.870 --> 00:35:41.050 align:middle line:84%
here's what I want you to know,
and here's our theme for today.

00:35:41.050 --> 00:35:43.660 align:middle line:90%
That path is already inside you.

00:35:43.660 --> 00:35:46.480 align:middle line:84%
There is an answer
already inside you,

00:35:46.480 --> 00:35:49.870 align:middle line:84%
and it's moment by
moment that we listen.

00:35:49.870 --> 00:35:52.250 align:middle line:90%
But it's really about listening.

00:35:52.250 --> 00:35:55.340 align:middle line:84%
It's really about learning
how to trust that voice.

00:35:55.340 --> 00:35:57.460 align:middle line:10%
So what I want to
talk about is, what

00:35:57.460 --> 00:35:59.740 align:middle line:10%
stops us from
trusting that voice?

00:35:59.740 --> 00:36:00.580 align:middle line:10%
We know this.

00:36:00.580 --> 00:36:01.930 align:middle line:10%
We affirm these things.

00:36:01.930 --> 00:36:03.130 align:middle line:10%
We say these things.

00:36:03.130 --> 00:36:04.810 align:middle line:10%
We believe in them.

00:36:04.810 --> 00:36:07.780 align:middle line:10%
What stops us from truly
trusting and listening

00:36:07.780 --> 00:36:09.070 align:middle line:10%
to that voice?

00:36:09.070 --> 00:36:11.920 align:middle line:10%
So I don't know about
you, but one thing I know

00:36:11.920 --> 00:36:15.220 align:middle line:10%
is that if you're not listening
to the voice of your love

00:36:15.220 --> 00:36:18.430 align:middle line:10%
and your heart and your
commitment and your dream

00:36:18.430 --> 00:36:22.325 align:middle line:10%
and your power, then you are
listening to somebody else.

00:36:22.325 --> 00:36:23.950 align:middle line:10%
And you're listening
to something else.

00:36:23.950 --> 00:36:26.590 align:middle line:10%
Because again, I deeply
believe we are living

00:36:26.590 --> 00:36:28.660 align:middle line:10%
in wildly inspired times.

00:36:28.660 --> 00:36:30.040 align:middle line:10%
Are we not?

00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:34.180 align:middle line:84%
We are living in very, very
different, crazy times.

00:36:34.180 --> 00:36:36.340 align:middle line:10%
I believe they're
wildly inspired times,

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:39.370 align:middle line:10%
and I believe it's
because we have wildly

00:36:39.370 --> 00:36:42.070 align:middle line:10%
inspired answers in us.

00:36:42.070 --> 00:36:46.060 align:middle line:10%
And it's time to live that dream
or that mission or that gift

00:36:46.060 --> 00:36:48.520 align:middle line:10%
that you have-- that thing
that someday you want to do.

00:36:48.520 --> 00:36:50.650 align:middle line:10%
That thing that you
always think about.

00:36:50.650 --> 00:36:52.570 align:middle line:10%
These are the times.

00:36:52.570 --> 00:36:54.520 align:middle line:10%
And so again, what
I was saying is,

00:36:54.520 --> 00:36:58.130 align:middle line:10%
if you're not
listening to yourself,

00:36:58.130 --> 00:36:59.717 align:middle line:10%
who are you listening to?

00:36:59.717 --> 00:37:01.300 align:middle line:10%
If you're not listening
to your heart,

00:37:01.300 --> 00:37:02.890 align:middle line:10%
you're not listening
to your light,

00:37:02.890 --> 00:37:04.330 align:middle line:10%
who are you listening to?

00:37:04.330 --> 00:37:06.580 align:middle line:84%
Are you listening to
the voice of the media?

00:37:06.580 --> 00:37:09.400 align:middle line:84%
Are you listening to
the voice of education?

00:37:09.400 --> 00:37:11.950 align:middle line:10%
Are you listening to
the voice of a parent?

00:37:11.950 --> 00:37:15.760 align:middle line:10%
If you know my story, I
was listening to my mother.

00:37:15.760 --> 00:37:17.380 align:middle line:90%
That's who I was listening to.

00:37:17.380 --> 00:37:18.213 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:37:18.213 --> 00:37:19.013 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:37:19.013 --> 00:37:21.400 align:middle line:84%
When we do have all those
different pieces of advice,

00:37:21.400 --> 00:37:24.490 align:middle line:84%
and especially people we
care about that we listen to,

00:37:24.490 --> 00:37:26.328 align:middle line:84%
and we grew up
listening to, and--

00:37:26.328 --> 00:37:28.120 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: They're in
our bloodstream, and--

00:37:28.120 --> 00:37:30.790 align:middle line:84%
the other thing I often
share with clients

00:37:30.790 --> 00:37:35.680 align:middle line:84%
also is, I never take
advice from unhappy people.

00:37:35.680 --> 00:37:38.110 align:middle line:84%
I never take advice from
unhappy people, or people

00:37:38.110 --> 00:37:40.120 align:middle line:90%
who aren't living their dreams.

00:37:40.120 --> 00:37:43.930 align:middle line:84%
If they're not really lit
up in living their dreams,

00:37:43.930 --> 00:37:45.520 align:middle line:90%
they may not know your path.

00:37:45.520 --> 00:37:47.440 align:middle line:84%
And some of the
people in our lives,

00:37:47.440 --> 00:37:50.090 align:middle line:84%
like our relatives or
whatever, they mean well.

00:37:50.090 --> 00:37:52.000 align:middle line:90%
They are speaking with love.

00:37:52.000 --> 00:37:53.810 align:middle line:90%
They want the best for you.

00:37:53.810 --> 00:37:55.960 align:middle line:84%
But they're speaking
with what they know.

00:37:55.960 --> 00:37:58.060 align:middle line:84%
And again, no one
knows your path.

00:37:58.060 --> 00:37:59.450 align:middle line:90%
You don't even know your path.

00:37:59.450 --> 00:38:00.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, so you're
talking about doing

00:38:00.520 --> 00:38:01.980 align:middle line:90%
a lot of self-guidance here.

00:38:01.980 --> 00:38:04.105 align:middle line:84%
And something that you talk
about in the book which

00:38:04.105 --> 00:38:06.070 align:middle line:84%
I like is, don't look
at what's falling apart.

00:38:06.070 --> 00:38:07.450 align:middle line:90%
Look at what's falling together.

00:38:07.450 --> 00:38:08.250 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:38:08.250 --> 00:38:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So most people look
at crisis as a dead end,

00:38:10.810 --> 00:38:12.250 align:middle line:90%
or there is no way out.

00:38:12.250 --> 00:38:13.060 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:38:13.060 --> 00:38:16.025 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then we look three,
four months later saying,

00:38:16.025 --> 00:38:17.900 align:middle line:84%
oh, it was the best
thing that ever happened.

00:38:17.900 --> 00:38:19.570 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: (LAUGHING) Exactly.

00:38:19.570 --> 00:38:21.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do we
train ourselves,

00:38:21.040 --> 00:38:22.930 align:middle line:84%
in that moment of
crisis to say, this

00:38:22.930 --> 00:38:25.060 align:middle line:84%
is the best thing that
could ever happen?

00:38:25.060 --> 00:38:26.210 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I wish we could.

00:38:26.210 --> 00:38:27.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I know.

00:38:27.010 --> 00:38:27.910 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I do.

00:38:27.910 --> 00:38:30.640 align:middle line:84%
I have th-- I remember
talking to a friend one time.

00:38:30.640 --> 00:38:32.432 align:middle line:84%
Somebody broke my
heart-- broke up with me.

00:38:32.432 --> 00:38:34.765 align:middle line:84%
And I remember talking to one
of my girlfriends, going--

00:38:34.765 --> 00:38:35.850 align:middle line:90%
[SNIFFS] you just watch.

00:38:35.850 --> 00:38:37.610 align:middle line:84%
This is going to be
a freaking miracle.

00:38:37.610 --> 00:38:38.745 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:38:38.745 --> 00:38:39.787 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You did say that?

00:38:39.787 --> 00:38:42.190 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So I knew
that intellectually,

00:38:42.190 --> 00:38:43.360 align:middle line:90%
and that's the thing.

00:38:43.360 --> 00:38:45.880 align:middle line:84%
Most of us know these
things intellectually.

00:38:45.880 --> 00:38:48.160 align:middle line:84%
We've read the self-help
books, or we've seen--

00:38:48.160 --> 00:38:49.360 align:middle line:90%
we've watched "Oprah."

00:38:49.360 --> 00:38:51.220 align:middle line:84%
We know these things
intellectually.

00:38:51.220 --> 00:38:52.595 align:middle line:84%
This is about
integrating it now.

00:38:52.595 --> 00:38:53.395 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:38:53.395 --> 00:38:55.540 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: This is about
really embodying it now.

00:38:55.540 --> 00:38:57.460 align:middle line:84%
So I would never
want to put pressure

00:38:57.460 --> 00:39:01.220 align:middle line:84%
on somebody who's in the
middle of something-- a crisis.

00:39:01.220 --> 00:39:03.800 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to put pressure
on them to feel great.

00:39:03.800 --> 00:39:04.600 align:middle line:90%
Feel positive.

00:39:04.600 --> 00:39:05.590 align:middle line:90%
Feel whatever.

00:39:05.590 --> 00:39:08.770 align:middle line:84%
I want to create safety for
them to feel whatever they're

00:39:08.770 --> 00:39:11.470 align:middle line:84%
feeling in that moment,
and to hold that awareness

00:39:11.470 --> 00:39:13.480 align:middle line:84%
that your brain is
telling you this

00:39:13.480 --> 00:39:15.260 align:middle line:84%
is the worst thing
that ever happened.

00:39:15.260 --> 00:39:16.460 align:middle line:90%
My life is over.

00:39:16.460 --> 00:39:17.260 align:middle line:90%
It's over.

00:39:17.260 --> 00:39:20.320 align:middle line:84%
And what I'd want you to know
is, one form of your life

00:39:20.320 --> 00:39:21.430 align:middle line:90%
may be over.

00:39:21.430 --> 00:39:24.300 align:middle line:90%
One expression might be over.

00:39:24.300 --> 00:39:26.860 align:middle line:84%
But it's so trite, but
it's like that caterpillar,

00:39:26.860 --> 00:39:27.940 align:middle line:90%
of the metamorphosis.

00:39:27.940 --> 00:39:32.200 align:middle line:84%
Of the caterpillar is
dying so that the butterfly

00:39:32.200 --> 00:39:33.100 align:middle line:90%
comes to life.

00:39:33.100 --> 00:39:33.760 align:middle line:90%
Right?

00:39:33.760 --> 00:39:34.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, yes.

00:39:34.270 --> 00:39:36.830 align:middle line:84%
And there's that, one door
closes and another one opens.

00:39:36.830 --> 00:39:37.120 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:39:37.120 --> 00:39:37.625 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a
lot of cliches here.

00:39:37.625 --> 00:39:38.550 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Yeah, we could
do all cliches now.

00:39:38.550 --> 00:39:38.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:38.690 --> 00:39:39.490 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:39:39.490 --> 00:39:43.520 align:middle line:84%
But the idea is, you said
the answer to how is yes.

00:39:43.520 --> 00:39:44.320 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:39:44.320 --> 00:39:45.653 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Tell me what that means.

00:39:45.653 --> 00:39:47.230 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So that's
a saying that--

00:39:47.230 --> 00:39:49.540 align:middle line:84%
I think it's the author
Peter Block who said it.

00:39:49.540 --> 00:39:52.150 align:middle line:84%
I love it, because I
teach it all the time.

00:39:52.150 --> 00:39:54.178 align:middle line:84%
And it's basically
that everybody's always

00:39:54.178 --> 00:39:55.970 align:middle line:84%
trying to figure out,
but how do I do this?

00:39:55.970 --> 00:39:56.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:39:56.230 --> 00:39:56.450 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: How do I this?

00:39:56.450 --> 00:39:56.500 align:middle line:90%
How do I get there?

00:39:56.500 --> 00:39:57.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I say that all the time.

00:39:57.820 --> 00:39:58.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah, we all do.

00:39:58.780 --> 00:40:00.350 align:middle line:84%
We all want to
figure out the path.

00:40:00.350 --> 00:40:02.860 align:middle line:84%
And again, I'm a
breadcrumb girl.

00:40:02.860 --> 00:40:04.120 align:middle line:90%
It's like the next step.

00:40:04.120 --> 00:40:07.120 align:middle line:90%
But the answer to how is yes.

00:40:07.120 --> 00:40:09.250 align:middle line:84%
And what that means
is, most of us

00:40:09.250 --> 00:40:13.630 align:middle line:84%
are trying to figure how to
get somewhere before we say yes

00:40:13.630 --> 00:40:14.920 align:middle line:90%
to what we really want.

00:40:14.920 --> 00:40:16.960 align:middle line:84%
If I can see how to
get there, then I'll

00:40:16.960 --> 00:40:18.860 align:middle line:90%
say yes to what I want.

00:40:18.860 --> 00:40:20.860 align:middle line:84%
And I really believe
that this is a path of,

00:40:20.860 --> 00:40:22.220 align:middle line:90%
you say yes first.

00:40:22.220 --> 00:40:23.020 align:middle line:90%
You have to--

00:40:23.020 --> 00:40:23.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And then how?

00:40:23.800 --> 00:40:25.133 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: And then the how come.

00:40:25.133 --> 00:40:26.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That makes sense.

00:40:26.380 --> 00:40:29.560 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So the example I use,
actually, is if, god forbid,

00:40:29.560 --> 00:40:33.220 align:middle line:84%
a mother saw her child
pinned under a bus,

00:40:33.220 --> 00:40:35.380 align:middle line:84%
she's not standing
there going, I wonder

00:40:35.380 --> 00:40:36.520 align:middle line:90%
how I'm going to do this.

00:40:36.520 --> 00:40:36.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:40:36.810 --> 00:40:38.893 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And will my
health insurance cover this,

00:40:38.893 --> 00:40:39.755 align:middle line:90%
and can I li--

00:40:39.755 --> 00:40:40.630 align:middle line:90%
she's not doing that.

00:40:40.630 --> 00:40:42.910 align:middle line:84%
She's like, I am going
to get my kid free.

00:40:42.910 --> 00:40:43.840 align:middle line:90%
That's all she knows.

00:40:43.840 --> 00:40:45.670 align:middle line:84%
She's saying yes,
and the how comes.

00:40:45.670 --> 00:40:47.500 align:middle line:90%
Supernatural strength comes.

00:40:47.500 --> 00:40:49.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, at the same
time-- so you say yes,

00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:51.400 align:middle line:84%
but then you do
need the roadmap.

00:40:51.400 --> 00:40:52.380 align:middle line:90%
You do need the how.

00:40:52.380 --> 00:40:54.808 align:middle line:84%
So after you have
an accident, you

00:40:54.808 --> 00:40:56.350 align:middle line:84%
say yes, I'm going
to heal from this.

00:40:56.350 --> 00:40:58.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes when you start recovering.

00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:00.890 align:middle line:84%
Now what am I going to do
about getting a new car?

00:41:00.890 --> 00:41:02.750 align:middle line:84%
How am I going to-- how am I
going to-- how am I going to--

00:41:02.750 --> 00:41:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:41:03.550 --> 00:41:06.970 align:middle line:84%
And I think, to your point about
the roadmap, is that I don't--

00:41:06.970 --> 00:41:09.640 align:middle line:84%
again, I'm always talking
about an inspired life, not

00:41:09.640 --> 00:41:10.510 align:middle line:90%
a linear life.

00:41:10.510 --> 00:41:13.030 align:middle line:84%
So if you want a linear life
where you can plan it all out

00:41:13.030 --> 00:41:15.790 align:middle line:84%
and map it all out,
that's a valid life.

00:41:15.790 --> 00:41:18.580 align:middle line:84%
It's a smaller life,
because what you can see

00:41:18.580 --> 00:41:21.430 align:middle line:84%
and what you can imagine
is again, sometimes

00:41:21.430 --> 00:41:23.200 align:middle line:90%
denying yourself something.

00:41:23.200 --> 00:41:25.810 align:middle line:84%
And so for an inspired
life, it doesn't work

00:41:25.810 --> 00:41:27.530 align:middle line:90%
through planning it all out.

00:41:27.530 --> 00:41:28.500 align:middle line:90%
It's going to wor--

00:41:28.500 --> 00:41:29.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:41:29.490 --> 00:41:30.820 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Everybody's
looking for answers.

00:41:30.820 --> 00:41:32.028 align:middle line:90%
And what I always tell them--

00:41:32.028 --> 00:41:34.910 align:middle line:84%
don't look for answers
for your whole life.

00:41:34.910 --> 00:41:36.040 align:middle line:90%
That's just too much.

00:41:36.040 --> 00:41:36.366 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:41:36.366 --> 00:41:38.074 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: What I want
you to look for is,

00:41:38.074 --> 00:41:39.010 align:middle line:90%
what's my next step?

00:41:39.010 --> 00:41:39.843 align:middle line:90%
What's my next step?

00:41:39.843 --> 00:41:40.643 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:41:40.643 --> 00:41:41.920 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: What's my next step?

00:41:41.920 --> 00:41:43.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because we
do tend to go so far.

00:41:43.510 --> 00:41:43.760 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Oh, god.

00:41:43.760 --> 00:41:44.750 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, if this
happens, then that.

00:41:44.750 --> 00:41:45.400 align:middle line:90%
Then this, then that.

00:41:45.400 --> 00:41:47.110 align:middle line:84%
Then this is going to wind
up, and then I'm dead.

00:41:47.110 --> 00:41:48.730 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I call that
playing mental chess.

00:41:48.730 --> 00:41:49.330 align:middle line:90%
That's what I do.

00:41:49.330 --> 00:41:50.720 align:middle line:90%
Now, if they do this, I do that.

00:41:50.720 --> 00:41:51.520 align:middle line:90%
I do this.

00:41:51.520 --> 00:41:54.170 align:middle line:84%
And we're planning with what we
know, or what we think we know.

00:41:54.170 --> 00:41:54.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:41:54.970 --> 00:41:57.130 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And life is
so much bigger and more

00:41:57.130 --> 00:41:59.290 align:middle line:90%
amazing than what we can know.

00:41:59.290 --> 00:42:01.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I get caught
with this all the time.

00:42:01.370 --> 00:42:02.800 align:middle line:90%
I try to predict the future--

00:42:02.800 --> 00:42:03.220 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Oh, yeah.

00:42:03.220 --> 00:42:04.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --or what's
going to happen.

00:42:04.150 --> 00:42:04.950 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:42:04.950 --> 00:42:07.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS] And my husband
says this me all the time.

00:42:07.450 --> 00:42:08.700 align:middle line:90%
You're mind reading, you know?

00:42:08.700 --> 00:42:10.340 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] And I'm like, I am?

00:42:10.340 --> 00:42:14.170 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, it's-- I go into that
default where I try to see it,

00:42:14.170 --> 00:42:16.240 align:middle line:84%
because I'm visual,
and if I don't see it,

00:42:16.240 --> 00:42:17.760 align:middle line:90%
I can't figure it out first.

00:42:17.760 --> 00:42:18.560 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:19.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It goes out to--

00:42:19.590 --> 00:42:20.450 align:middle line:90%
this table.

00:42:20.450 --> 00:42:22.370 align:middle line:84%
There's only this table, because
I'm going to imagine it first.

00:42:22.370 --> 00:42:25.080 align:middle line:84%
And I need to imagine it first
in order for it to happen.

00:42:25.080 --> 00:42:25.880 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:42:25.880 --> 00:42:31.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But leaping right into
it happening isn't my lead.

00:42:31.110 --> 00:42:31.966 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:42:31.966 --> 00:42:32.766 align:middle line:90%
Mm-hmm.

00:42:32.766 --> 00:42:34.893 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so how would
you coach me if I say,

00:42:34.893 --> 00:42:36.810 align:middle line:84%
OK, well, I don't know
how to figure this out.

00:42:36.810 --> 00:42:37.980 align:middle line:90%
But I know what I want.

00:42:37.980 --> 00:42:38.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:42:38.780 --> 00:42:39.360 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:42:39.360 --> 00:42:40.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Would you
just say, imagine it?

00:42:40.890 --> 00:42:42.650 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So I think
the first thing is,

00:42:42.650 --> 00:42:44.397 align:middle line:90%
I want to get you feeling it.

00:42:44.397 --> 00:42:45.980 align:middle line:84%
I want to get you
in the desire of it.

00:42:45.980 --> 00:42:47.438 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What that
feels like, yeah.

00:42:47.438 --> 00:42:49.460 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Because again,
most people immediately

00:42:49.460 --> 00:42:52.970 align:middle line:84%
start off with, I want a
really successful business.

00:42:52.970 --> 00:42:55.700 align:middle line:84%
And then they
immediately go into,

00:42:55.700 --> 00:42:58.522 align:middle line:84%
oh, but my finances
are a mess, and I

00:42:58.522 --> 00:42:59.730 align:middle line:90%
don't know how to get a loan.

00:42:59.730 --> 00:43:01.460 align:middle line:84%
And I can't do this,
and I can't do that.

00:43:01.460 --> 00:43:04.160 align:middle line:84%
So they immediately start
focusing on the obstacles.

00:43:04.160 --> 00:43:05.870 align:middle line:84%
I want to get you
focused on the desire.

00:43:05.870 --> 00:43:08.237 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to have you tell
me more about what you want,

00:43:08.237 --> 00:43:10.070 align:middle line:84%
and more about what you
want, so that you're

00:43:10.070 --> 00:43:11.520 align:middle line:90%
in the feeling of it.

00:43:11.520 --> 00:43:14.840 align:middle line:84%
And from that feeling, we're
going to come up with, OK,

00:43:14.840 --> 00:43:16.550 align:middle line:84%
what would feel
good as a next step?

00:43:16.550 --> 00:43:19.310 align:middle line:84%
What would feel good as
a-- to approach this?

00:43:19.310 --> 00:43:21.390 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So go after
the why you want it

00:43:21.390 --> 00:43:23.160 align:middle line:84%
and the bigger purpose
connected to it.

00:43:23.160 --> 00:43:23.960 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:43:23.960 --> 00:43:26.480 align:middle line:84%
And the how fun it
would be, and how amaz--

00:43:26.480 --> 00:43:27.470 align:middle line:90%
what if it could work?

00:43:27.470 --> 00:43:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fun.

00:43:28.270 --> 00:43:28.460 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:43:28.460 --> 00:43:29.930 align:middle line:90%
What if it could work?

00:43:29.930 --> 00:43:32.870 align:middle line:84%
Like I always have to remember,
because I still fall into this.

00:43:32.870 --> 00:43:35.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm preparing for a
seminar or something like--

00:43:35.360 --> 00:43:36.330 align:middle line:90%
and my mind's going--

00:43:36.330 --> 00:43:37.220 align:middle line:90%
I'll be flying.

00:43:37.220 --> 00:43:37.880 align:middle line:90%
I'll be flying there.

00:43:37.880 --> 00:43:39.672 align:middle line:84%
I'm like-- part of my
brain is going, well,

00:43:39.672 --> 00:43:41.365 align:middle line:84%
it's international,
so if you screw up,

00:43:41.365 --> 00:43:42.740 align:middle line:84%
you never have to
go there again.

00:43:42.740 --> 00:43:47.090 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] So that's my inner
self-doubt going, if you really

00:43:47.090 --> 00:43:50.000 align:middle line:84%
mess this up, you never have
to go to that country again.

00:43:50.000 --> 00:43:53.870 align:middle line:84%
And so-- but I have to
change that self-talk to,

00:43:53.870 --> 00:43:55.275 align:middle line:90%
what if it was phenomenal?

00:43:55.275 --> 00:43:56.150 align:middle line:90%
What if it was great?

00:43:56.150 --> 00:43:57.390 align:middle line:90%
How would that feel?

00:43:57.390 --> 00:43:58.820 align:middle line:90%
How exciting would that be?

00:43:58.820 --> 00:44:01.040 align:middle line:84%
That more people are
now doing their dreams

00:44:01.040 --> 00:44:03.350 align:middle line:84%
and using their gifts
and being extraordinary.

00:44:03.350 --> 00:44:05.120 align:middle line:84%
What would that
feel-- so it helps

00:44:05.120 --> 00:44:07.170 align:middle line:90%
me get into that feeling of it.

00:44:07.170 --> 00:44:09.350 align:middle line:84%
And from that feeling, I
can accomplish anything.

00:44:09.350 --> 00:44:11.058 align:middle line:90%
And I will know a next step.

00:44:11.058 --> 00:44:13.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you still have
negative self-talk too.

00:44:13.100 --> 00:44:13.950 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [SCOFFS] Yeah.

00:44:13.950 --> 00:44:14.260 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:44:14.260 --> 00:44:14.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A lot.

00:44:14.570 --> 00:44:15.890 align:middle line:84%
That's how you write
the books, right?

00:44:15.890 --> 00:44:17.350 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's why
I'm a great teacher.

00:44:17.350 --> 00:44:18.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:18.150 --> 00:44:21.570 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Because again,
because of I think that again,

00:44:21.570 --> 00:44:22.370 align:middle line:90%
I think this--

00:44:22.370 --> 00:44:25.010 align:middle line:84%
if you are going to grow
for the rest of your life,

00:44:25.010 --> 00:44:27.360 align:middle line:84%
if you are going to
dinner or something new,

00:44:27.360 --> 00:44:28.790 align:middle line:84%
if you are going
to stay inspired,

00:44:28.790 --> 00:44:30.440 align:middle line:84%
you're always
going to your edge.

00:44:30.440 --> 00:44:32.210 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to
your edge, you're

00:44:32.210 --> 00:44:34.340 align:middle line:90%
always going to face fear.

00:44:34.340 --> 00:44:37.810 align:middle line:84%
I personally don't trust
experts that say, oh, I

00:44:37.810 --> 00:44:39.680 align:middle line:90%
don't have any fears ever.

00:44:39.680 --> 00:44:41.420 align:middle line:84%
It's like, well, then
you're not alive.

00:44:41.420 --> 00:44:41.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:41.620 --> 00:44:42.120 align:middle line:90%
It is--

00:44:42.120 --> 00:44:42.920 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: They're not alive.

00:44:42.920 --> 00:44:43.730 align:middle line:90%
It's part of life.

00:44:43.730 --> 00:44:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:44:44.530 --> 00:44:47.902 align:middle line:84%
And it's not something that
we can reverse engineer

00:44:47.902 --> 00:44:50.360 align:middle line:84%
and say, OK, well, I'm just
never going to have fear again,

00:44:50.360 --> 00:44:52.740 align:middle line:84%
and really live in this place
of total, complete peace.

00:44:52.740 --> 00:44:53.540 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Right.

00:44:53.540 --> 00:44:54.050 align:middle line:90%
I think it's--

00:44:54.050 --> 00:44:55.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's there for a reason.

00:44:55.010 --> 00:44:56.750 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: It is
there for a reason.

00:44:56.750 --> 00:45:00.740 align:middle line:84%
And my fear has made me dig
deeper into my spirituality,

00:45:00.740 --> 00:45:04.460 align:middle line:84%
and make me dig deeper
into my real beliefs,

00:45:04.460 --> 00:45:06.590 align:middle line:84%
and what I will commit
to in this lifetime.

00:45:06.590 --> 00:45:07.820 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't let me be casual.

00:45:07.820 --> 00:45:08.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:08.620 --> 00:45:10.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: It doesn't
let me coast.

00:45:10.200 --> 00:45:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And again, the one thing I
will say that I have from it,

00:45:13.460 --> 00:45:17.000 align:middle line:84%
though, is you start having a
track record of having trusted

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:19.130 align:middle line:84%
your inner voice
and your instincts,

00:45:19.130 --> 00:45:20.152 align:middle line:90%
and that it did work.

00:45:20.152 --> 00:45:22.610 align:middle line:84%
And you didn't go bankrupt,
and you're not eating cat food.

00:45:22.610 --> 00:45:23.080 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:45:23.080 --> 00:45:23.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:45:23.610 --> 00:45:25.880 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And no one you
love is eating cat food--

00:45:25.880 --> 00:45:27.450 align:middle line:90%
except your cats.

00:45:27.450 --> 00:45:30.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then it eventually
works out, and have a track

00:45:30.050 --> 00:45:31.240 align:middle line:90%
record of it working out.

00:45:31.240 --> 00:45:32.040 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:45:32.040 --> 00:45:34.980 align:middle line:84%
So at least I have that
sanity now to say, OK, Tam,

00:45:34.980 --> 00:45:36.750 align:middle line:90%
you're scared out of your mind.

00:45:36.750 --> 00:45:38.510 align:middle line:84%
You're telling
yourself scary stories.

00:45:38.510 --> 00:45:41.270 align:middle line:84%
But you know these
principles work.

00:45:41.270 --> 00:45:42.080 align:middle line:90%
You know they work.

00:45:42.080 --> 00:45:42.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:45:42.680 --> 00:45:44.280 align:middle line:84%
And you have no idea
how it's going to work,

00:45:44.280 --> 00:45:45.620 align:middle line:90%
but it has worked in the past.

00:45:45.620 --> 00:45:46.040 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Always.

00:45:46.040 --> 00:45:47.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's why
you are where you are.

00:45:47.570 --> 00:45:48.370 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:45:48.370 --> 00:45:50.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you've
just got to keep going.

00:45:50.160 --> 00:45:53.180 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And the reason that,
again, I don't map it out,

00:45:53.180 --> 00:45:54.980 align:middle line:84%
is because sometimes
we're going someplace

00:45:54.980 --> 00:45:56.960 align:middle line:90%
we never thought we'd go.

00:45:56.960 --> 00:46:02.900 align:middle line:84%
For instance, I speak
all over about listening

00:46:02.900 --> 00:46:04.610 align:middle line:90%
to an inner voice.

00:46:04.610 --> 00:46:06.295 align:middle line:84%
That is the last
thing on the planet

00:46:06.295 --> 00:46:08.670 align:middle line:84%
I would have ever thought I
was going to do with my life.

00:46:08.670 --> 00:46:09.800 align:middle line:90%
I grew up orthodox Jewish.

00:46:09.800 --> 00:46:10.760 align:middle line:90%
I went to Harvard Law School.

00:46:10.760 --> 00:46:11.930 align:middle line:90%
I made fun of people like that.

00:46:11.930 --> 00:46:12.395 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:46:12.395 --> 00:46:13.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:46:13.130 --> 00:46:14.350 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I made fun
of people like that.

00:46:14.350 --> 00:46:15.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Uh-huh.

00:46:15.470 --> 00:46:16.940 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I used to have
it on my answering machine,

00:46:16.940 --> 00:46:19.190 align:middle line:84%
like "and trust your inner
journey" or something.

00:46:19.190 --> 00:46:21.690 align:middle line:84%
And my friends would be like,
what the hell happened to you?

00:46:21.690 --> 00:46:22.860 align:middle line:90%
You used to be normal.

00:46:22.860 --> 00:46:25.340 align:middle line:84%
And just-- so my
point is, sometimes

00:46:25.340 --> 00:46:27.380 align:middle line:84%
you can't map it out,
because you don't even

00:46:27.380 --> 00:46:28.910 align:middle line:90%
know where you're meant to go.

00:46:28.910 --> 00:46:31.820 align:middle line:84%
I've discovered different
capacities in myself,

00:46:31.820 --> 00:46:35.180 align:middle line:84%
and different belief systems,
and different abilities

00:46:35.180 --> 00:46:36.010 align:middle line:90%
than I knew I--

00:46:36.010 --> 00:46:37.870 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know I
was a speaker ever.

00:46:37.870 --> 00:46:38.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ever.

00:46:38.670 --> 00:46:39.780 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Ever.

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:40.580 align:middle line:90%
I knew I like--

00:46:40.580 --> 00:46:42.380 align:middle line:84%
I thought-- or
even with coaching,

00:46:42.380 --> 00:46:44.778 align:middle line:90%
I just thought I was needy.

00:46:44.778 --> 00:46:45.820 align:middle line:90%
I like talking to people.

00:46:45.820 --> 00:46:46.930 align:middle line:90%
I just thought I was needy.

00:46:46.930 --> 00:46:47.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:46:47.270 --> 00:46:48.710 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Who knew
it was a talent?

00:46:48.710 --> 00:46:49.265 align:middle line:90%
I'm relational.

00:46:49.265 --> 00:46:49.670 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love it.

00:46:49.670 --> 00:46:50.470 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:46:50.470 --> 00:46:51.615 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I love it.

00:46:51.615 --> 00:46:53.240 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at
Tama we're talking

00:46:53.240 --> 00:46:56.240 align:middle line:84%
about the voices in our head and
the stories we tell ourselves.

00:46:56.240 --> 00:46:57.280 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:46:57.280 --> 00:46:59.410 align:middle line:84%
- So I'll give you an
example of how stories work.

00:46:59.410 --> 00:47:01.630 align:middle line:90%
It's one of my good examples.

00:47:01.630 --> 00:47:03.910 align:middle line:84%
When I met my partner
many, many years ago--

00:47:03.910 --> 00:47:05.690 align:middle line:90%
Paul, who's back there--

00:47:05.690 --> 00:47:09.530 align:middle line:84%
and we met at a conference
many, many years ago.

00:47:09.530 --> 00:47:12.790 align:middle line:84%
And we were at this conference,
and we're walking together.

00:47:12.790 --> 00:47:14.890 align:middle line:84%
And when I'm relaxed,
I'm just chirping away.

00:47:14.890 --> 00:47:17.530 align:middle line:84%
I'm like, [CHIRPING AWAY]
yakking away.

00:47:17.530 --> 00:47:19.120 align:middle line:90%
And he's very quiet.

00:47:19.120 --> 00:47:20.440 align:middle line:90%
So he's very quiet.

00:47:20.440 --> 00:47:23.120 align:middle line:84%
And so my immediate
thought was like, ooh,

00:47:23.120 --> 00:47:24.880 align:middle line:90%
he's a good listener.

00:47:24.880 --> 00:47:26.800 align:middle line:90%
This is going to work.

00:47:26.800 --> 00:47:28.120 align:middle line:90%
So that's my first thought.

00:47:28.120 --> 00:47:29.350 align:middle line:90%
That's great, right?

00:47:29.350 --> 00:47:32.620 align:middle line:84%
Then I start-- you know how
you start hitting something,

00:47:32.620 --> 00:47:35.000 align:middle line:90%
and some fear starts coming in?

00:47:35.000 --> 00:47:37.330 align:middle line:84%
So all of a sudden, this
fear starts coming in of--

00:47:37.330 --> 00:47:40.450 align:middle line:90%
[GASPS] maybe I'm boring him.

00:47:40.450 --> 00:47:42.565 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I'm boring
him into a stupor.

00:47:42.565 --> 00:47:43.640 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:47:43.640 --> 00:47:44.440 align:middle line:90%


00:47:44.440 --> 00:47:47.170 align:middle line:84%
So that's the second
thought that comes in.

00:47:47.170 --> 00:47:51.580 align:middle line:84%
And then all the crap from my
past, like past boyfriends,

00:47:51.580 --> 00:47:54.040 align:middle line:84%
and past relationships
start coming to my brain.

00:47:54.040 --> 00:47:55.870 align:middle line:90%
Like, you're so intense.

00:47:55.870 --> 00:47:57.600 align:middle line:90%
You're so intense.

00:47:57.600 --> 00:47:59.800 align:middle line:84%
So I'm having this
conversation in my head now.

00:47:59.800 --> 00:48:00.980 align:middle line:90%
Like, I am not that intense.

00:48:00.980 --> 00:48:01.490 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:01.490 --> 00:48:02.290 align:middle line:90%
You know?

00:48:02.290 --> 00:48:04.810 align:middle line:90%
I am not.

00:48:04.810 --> 00:48:07.530 align:middle line:84%
And so I'm just having
this thing, and it's like--

00:48:07.530 --> 00:48:11.440 align:middle line:84%
and I'm thinking,
I'm not that intense.

00:48:11.440 --> 00:48:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And I'm thinking, I could
do better than this.

00:48:13.960 --> 00:48:14.777 align:middle line:90%
I really could.

00:48:14.777 --> 00:48:16.360 align:middle line:84%
While all Paul is
done has been quiet.

00:48:16.360 --> 00:48:17.568 align:middle line:90%
That is all that is going on.

00:48:17.568 --> 00:48:19.300 align:middle line:90%
The man has not said a word--

00:48:19.300 --> 00:48:20.310 align:middle line:90%
not said a word.

00:48:20.310 --> 00:48:23.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm immediately-- now I am
judging the hell out of him,

00:48:23.020 --> 00:48:23.230 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:48:23.230 --> 00:48:25.140 align:middle line:84%
Now I'm thinking, I
could do bet-- you know,

00:48:25.140 --> 00:48:27.070 align:middle line:90%
he's not even that good looking.

00:48:27.070 --> 00:48:27.970 align:middle line:90%
I could do better.

00:48:27.970 --> 00:48:30.190 align:middle line:84%
I'm going through this
whole thing in my head.

00:48:30.190 --> 00:48:33.550 align:middle line:84%
All that has happened in reality
is he hasn't said a word.

00:48:33.550 --> 00:48:35.950 align:middle line:90%
I have gone all over the place.

00:48:35.950 --> 00:48:39.700 align:middle line:84%
Thank god-- thank god in
that particular moment

00:48:39.700 --> 00:48:43.470 align:middle line:84%
I had the wisdom or presence
of mind to actually ask him

00:48:43.470 --> 00:48:46.570 align:middle line:84%
what was going on, instead of
having this war in my head.

00:48:46.570 --> 00:48:50.530 align:middle line:84%
And I had just said, well,
I noticed that you're quiet.

00:48:50.530 --> 00:48:53.110 align:middle line:84%
I noticed that you're quiet,
and I'm just wondering,

00:48:53.110 --> 00:48:54.110 align:middle line:90%
is something going on?

00:48:54.110 --> 00:48:54.910 align:middle line:90%
Whatever.

00:48:54.910 --> 00:48:56.170 align:middle line:90%
And he was really sweet.

00:48:56.170 --> 00:49:01.390 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, to be
honest with you, I'm nervous.

00:49:01.390 --> 00:49:04.930 align:middle line:84%
You're a beautiful woman,
and you're intelligent,

00:49:04.930 --> 00:49:07.120 align:middle line:90%
and I'm a little nervous.

00:49:07.120 --> 00:49:08.320 align:middle line:90%
And I'm like, oh.

00:49:08.320 --> 00:49:09.526 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:49:09.526 --> 00:49:10.430 align:middle line:90%


00:49:10.430 --> 00:49:12.090 align:middle line:90%
Oh!

00:49:12.090 --> 00:49:14.440 align:middle line:90%
What a superior individual.

00:49:14.440 --> 00:49:16.220 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:49:16.220 --> 00:49:17.230 align:middle line:90%
This!

00:49:17.230 --> 00:49:18.937 align:middle line:90%
This could so work.

00:49:18.937 --> 00:49:20.765 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:49:20.765 --> 00:49:22.140 align:middle line:90%


00:49:22.140 --> 00:49:24.185 align:middle line:84%
Isn't that a great
example of story?

00:49:24.185 --> 00:49:25.780 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:49:25.780 --> 00:49:28.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I love that
story of all the things

00:49:28.020 --> 00:49:30.580 align:middle line:84%
that you made up
about that meeting.

00:49:30.580 --> 00:49:31.680 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine now.

00:49:31.680 --> 00:49:32.480 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:49:32.480 --> 00:49:33.430 align:middle line:90%
Everything's fine now.

00:49:33.430 --> 00:49:34.950 align:middle line:84%
But I still make up
stories in my head.

00:49:34.950 --> 00:49:35.810 align:middle line:90%
We all do.

00:49:35.810 --> 00:49:36.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:49:36.210 --> 00:49:36.810 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: We all do.

00:49:36.810 --> 00:49:37.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

00:49:37.600 --> 00:49:40.100 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And I think that what
I really want people to know

00:49:40.100 --> 00:49:42.750 align:middle line:84%
is that you are living,
every single day,

00:49:42.750 --> 00:49:44.370 align:middle line:90%
the stories you tell yourself.

00:49:44.370 --> 00:49:46.980 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: My god, if my
steering wheel could talk,

00:49:46.980 --> 00:49:47.964 align:middle line:90%
it would be bad.

00:49:47.964 --> 00:49:48.456 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:49:48.456 --> 00:49:49.456 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It would be bad.

00:49:49.456 --> 00:49:51.120 align:middle line:90%
But then, I need to talk it out.

00:49:51.120 --> 00:49:53.300 align:middle line:84%
I need to get it out
first, and then I'm calm.

00:49:53.300 --> 00:49:54.100 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm-hmm.

00:49:54.100 --> 00:49:54.900 align:middle line:90%
Mm-hmm.

00:49:54.900 --> 00:49:56.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Sometimes we
just need to hear it.

00:49:56.800 --> 00:49:57.600 align:middle line:90%
Speak it.

00:49:57.600 --> 00:49:59.460 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Or sometimes,
you don't even know that--

00:49:59.460 --> 00:50:00.835 align:middle line:84%
again, you think
the story you're

00:50:00.835 --> 00:50:02.490 align:middle line:90%
telling yourself is real.

00:50:02.490 --> 00:50:04.860 align:middle line:84%
You think that's reality,
and you don't realize

00:50:04.860 --> 00:50:06.960 align:middle line:90%
it's an unconscious story.

00:50:06.960 --> 00:50:07.840 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very true.

00:50:07.840 --> 00:50:11.010 align:middle line:84%
So in your book, you talk about
being unfaithful to yourself--

00:50:11.010 --> 00:50:12.120 align:middle line:90%
being sporadic.

00:50:12.120 --> 00:50:13.170 align:middle line:90%
What do you mean by that?

00:50:13.170 --> 00:50:13.970 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:50:13.970 --> 00:50:17.220 align:middle line:84%
I have a chapter of, dare
to be unfaithful, sporadic,

00:50:17.220 --> 00:50:19.800 align:middle line:90%
and unusually true to yourself.

00:50:19.800 --> 00:50:21.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:50:21.660 --> 00:50:23.580 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And it's
because I wanted

00:50:23.580 --> 00:50:27.320 align:middle line:84%
to give people permission
to experiment and explore.

00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:29.040 align:middle line:84%
I have a lot of
clients who are type A,

00:50:29.040 --> 00:50:30.490 align:middle line:84%
and they want to
force everything.

00:50:30.490 --> 00:50:31.290 align:middle line:90%
Like, that's it.

00:50:31.290 --> 00:50:34.972 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to meditate now, every
single day for an hour and 1/2.

00:50:34.972 --> 00:50:37.020 align:middle line:84%
Or I'm going to write
the Great American Novel.

00:50:37.020 --> 00:50:41.100 align:middle line:84%
And I want people to have
the breathing room to make

00:50:41.100 --> 00:50:43.500 align:middle line:90%
a commitment and break it.

00:50:43.500 --> 00:50:45.810 align:middle line:84%
To explore, to experiment,
because sometimes you're

00:50:45.810 --> 00:50:48.510 align:middle line:84%
making a commitment from your
head from what you think you

00:50:48.510 --> 00:50:49.540 align:middle line:90%
should do.

00:50:49.540 --> 00:50:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And I want to give you that
breathing room to choose again.

00:50:52.700 --> 00:50:53.770 align:middle line:90%
Choose again.

00:50:53.770 --> 00:50:54.570 align:middle line:90%
Choose again.

00:50:54.570 --> 00:50:56.910 align:middle line:84%
Sometime-- we start a
diet and we mess up,

00:50:56.910 --> 00:50:57.990 align:middle line:90%
and we think, forget it.

00:50:57.990 --> 00:50:58.980 align:middle line:90%
I'm never going to do that.

00:50:58.980 --> 00:50:59.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:50:59.250 --> 00:51:01.915 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And it's like, I want
this to be more self-loving.

00:51:01.915 --> 00:51:04.290 align:middle line:84%
I want it to be something that
you have permission always

00:51:04.290 --> 00:51:07.380 align:middle line:84%
to just start right now to
choose again, and to not worry

00:51:07.380 --> 00:51:10.920 align:middle line:84%
about being linear or staying
with the one commitment

00:51:10.920 --> 00:51:13.740 align:middle line:84%
you set, but maybe the higher
commitment, and the higher

00:51:13.740 --> 00:51:15.960 align:middle line:84%
goal, and to have
that experimentation.

00:51:15.960 --> 00:51:18.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've heard the
phrase of making your life

00:51:18.570 --> 00:51:19.480 align:middle line:90%
unrecognizable.

00:51:19.480 --> 00:51:20.280 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Mm.

00:51:20.280 --> 00:51:24.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that idea of being
unfaithful to what you thought

00:51:24.240 --> 00:51:29.220 align:middle line:84%
was so true, and changing it
so that It looks so radically

00:51:29.220 --> 00:51:31.050 align:middle line:90%
different, but in a good way.

00:51:31.050 --> 00:51:31.130 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:51:31.130 --> 00:51:32.713 align:middle line:84%
In a good way, you're
following again.

00:51:32.713 --> 00:51:34.590 align:middle line:84%
Because again, everybody
has their advice.

00:51:34.590 --> 00:51:37.900 align:middle line:84%
When I started writing, I joined
some writers' support group.

00:51:37.900 --> 00:51:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And I had some
curmudgeonly old man

00:51:39.560 --> 00:51:41.560 align:middle line:84%
that told me, if you
really want to be a writer,

00:51:41.560 --> 00:51:43.230 align:middle line:84%
you have to write
every single day.

00:51:43.230 --> 00:51:46.350 align:middle line:84%
And I panicked because I wasn't
writing every single day,

00:51:46.350 --> 00:51:47.640 align:middle line:90%
and I wasn't doing it right.

00:51:47.640 --> 00:51:50.050 align:middle line:84%
I've still never written
every single day.

00:51:50.050 --> 00:51:51.930 align:middle line:90%
And so I just--

00:51:51.930 --> 00:51:54.292 align:middle line:84%
I think that you have to
find your own chemistry

00:51:54.292 --> 00:51:55.125 align:middle line:90%
and your own rhythm.

00:51:55.125 --> 00:51:55.925 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:55.925 --> 00:51:58.500 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And you have to have
that experimentation to do it.

00:51:58.500 --> 00:51:59.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:51:59.310 --> 00:52:01.620 align:middle line:84%
So you talk about something
called a Win List.

00:52:01.620 --> 00:52:02.680 align:middle line:90%
What is a Win List?

00:52:02.680 --> 00:52:04.590 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: So Win List
is a technique I use.

00:52:04.590 --> 00:52:07.020 align:middle line:84%
Again, it's in my
books, and it's also

00:52:07.020 --> 00:52:09.720 align:middle line:90%
on my website, tamakieves.com.

00:52:09.720 --> 00:52:12.390 align:middle line:84%
But it's a technique
I use with my clients.

00:52:12.390 --> 00:52:16.423 align:middle line:84%
And what it is is, many of us
who are in uncertainty of--

00:52:16.423 --> 00:52:18.090 align:middle line:84%
or maybe you're doing
your own business.

00:52:18.090 --> 00:52:20.700 align:middle line:84%
Your mind is racing and racing
about all you haven't done,

00:52:20.700 --> 00:52:22.800 align:middle line:84%
all you haven't accomplished,
how you're not making progress,

00:52:22.800 --> 00:52:24.175 align:middle line:84%
how you're not
getting there, how

00:52:24.175 --> 00:52:27.150 align:middle line:84%
you're cellulite is making
progress, but you're not.

00:52:27.150 --> 00:52:28.730 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] And so--

00:52:28.730 --> 00:52:29.808 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:52:29.808 --> 00:52:31.350 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: The Win
List is a technique

00:52:31.350 --> 00:52:35.190 align:middle line:84%
where I ask you to write maybe
five to 10 wins each day.

00:52:35.190 --> 00:52:39.990 align:middle line:84%
And what a win is is some
kind of progress-- some kind

00:52:39.990 --> 00:52:41.190 align:middle line:90%
of forward movement.

00:52:41.190 --> 00:52:44.160 align:middle line:84%
And some of it can be
external, like, OK, I

00:52:44.160 --> 00:52:46.320 align:middle line:84%
called that person I was
supposed to call today.

00:52:46.320 --> 00:52:48.090 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm even
more interested

00:52:48.090 --> 00:52:50.760 align:middle line:84%
in is internal
progress-- the things

00:52:50.760 --> 00:52:52.800 align:middle line:84%
you might normally
never recognize.

00:52:52.800 --> 00:52:55.380 align:middle line:84%
For instance, I'm
usually depressed

00:52:55.380 --> 00:52:57.510 align:middle line:90%
for 30 minutes when I wake up.

00:52:57.510 --> 00:53:00.395 align:middle line:84%
But today, I was
depressed for 29 minutes.

00:53:00.395 --> 00:53:01.770 align:middle line:84%
That's going to
go on a Win List.

00:53:01.770 --> 00:53:03.750 align:middle line:90%
And again, you might think--

00:53:03.750 --> 00:53:06.600 align:middle line:84%
most of us are so linear, we
think, oh, that's not progress.

00:53:06.600 --> 00:53:09.750 align:middle line:84%
But on this kind of
journey, it's all internal.

00:53:09.750 --> 00:53:11.400 align:middle line:90%
And it's the internal shifts.

00:53:11.400 --> 00:53:14.680 align:middle line:84%
And so I want to have
people credit themselves

00:53:14.680 --> 00:53:15.930 align:middle line:90%
for the things they are doing.

00:53:15.930 --> 00:53:19.730 align:middle line:84%
Like, I had the courage to
tell my husband the truth.

00:53:19.730 --> 00:53:22.572 align:middle line:84%
I backed down in the middle
of it, but at least I started.

00:53:22.572 --> 00:53:23.780 align:middle line:90%
So that goes on the Win List.

00:53:23.780 --> 00:53:24.120 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

00:53:24.120 --> 00:53:25.578 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: I wrote
my damn Win List.

00:53:25.578 --> 00:53:26.610 align:middle line:90%
That goes on there.

00:53:26.610 --> 00:53:27.080 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:53:27.080 --> 00:53:27.170 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:53:27.170 --> 00:53:28.090 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I wrote on my Win List.

00:53:28.090 --> 00:53:28.890 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:53:28.890 --> 00:53:30.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or that you
went to do something

00:53:30.960 --> 00:53:32.580 align:middle line:84%
that you usually
have as a habit,

00:53:32.580 --> 00:53:34.560 align:middle line:84%
and you just stop
for a few minutes.

00:53:34.560 --> 00:53:35.360 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:53:35.360 --> 00:53:35.820 align:middle line:90%
Perfect.

00:53:35.820 --> 00:53:36.040 align:middle line:90%
Perfect.

00:53:36.040 --> 00:53:38.225 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Like eating chocolate
cake or something like that.

00:53:38.225 --> 00:53:38.310 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Perfect.

00:53:38.310 --> 00:53:39.270 align:middle line:90%
I was conscious.

00:53:39.270 --> 00:53:42.150 align:middle line:84%
I still caved, but I
was conscious this time.

00:53:42.150 --> 00:53:43.650 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So does it
help you actually

00:53:43.650 --> 00:53:45.602 align:middle line:90%
get rid of the bad habit?

00:53:45.602 --> 00:53:46.560 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes, it does.

00:53:46.560 --> 00:53:49.320 align:middle line:84%
Because what you're doing is
you're building the self-love,

00:53:49.320 --> 00:53:51.300 align:middle line:84%
and you're building
the sense of progress.

00:53:51.300 --> 00:53:54.600 align:middle line:84%
And bad habits come
from bad self-talk.

00:53:54.600 --> 00:53:56.455 align:middle line:84%
Bad habits come from,
I feel like a loser.

00:53:56.455 --> 00:53:58.080 align:middle line:84%
I feel like I'm never
getting anywhere.

00:53:58.080 --> 00:54:00.070 align:middle line:84%
Only chocolate cake is
going to save me now.

00:54:00.070 --> 00:54:00.870 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:54:00.870 --> 00:54:03.162 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: But if I'm feeling
like, yeah, I am doing it.

00:54:03.162 --> 00:54:04.410 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I am getting better.

00:54:04.410 --> 00:54:06.310 align:middle line:84%
Oh my god, I did
stand up for myself.

00:54:06.310 --> 00:54:07.380 align:middle line:90%
I did apply this.

00:54:07.380 --> 00:54:08.880 align:middle line:84%
And the other thing
about a Win List

00:54:08.880 --> 00:54:11.190 align:middle line:84%
is, sometimes what goes
on it is a moment when

00:54:11.190 --> 00:54:13.410 align:middle line:84%
you felt connected
to maybe the universe

00:54:13.410 --> 00:54:14.870 align:middle line:90%
or spirit or something.

00:54:14.870 --> 00:54:17.190 align:middle line:84%
Where all of a sudden you
had that thought and somebody

00:54:17.190 --> 00:54:18.000 align:middle line:90%
called to you.

00:54:18.000 --> 00:54:19.958 align:middle line:84%
So you feel like, oh,
maybe I'm not alone here.

00:54:19.958 --> 00:54:21.570 align:middle line:90%
Maybe there is a higher plan.

00:54:21.570 --> 00:54:22.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Where do you keep this?

00:54:22.250 --> 00:54:23.122 align:middle line:90%
Somewhere visible?

00:54:23.122 --> 00:54:24.330 align:middle line:90%
Or is it something that you--

00:54:24.330 --> 00:54:25.538 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: That's a cool idea.

00:54:25.538 --> 00:54:27.180 align:middle line:90%
I just journal it on anything.

00:54:27.180 --> 00:54:28.845 align:middle line:84%
When I'm a nut,
anything will do.

00:54:28.845 --> 00:54:29.310 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:54:29.310 --> 00:54:31.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you help
people with writing books?

00:54:31.170 --> 00:54:32.270 align:middle line:90%
Do you help them with talks?

00:54:32.270 --> 00:54:33.395 align:middle line:90%
What do you help them with?

00:54:33.395 --> 00:54:34.290 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:54:34.290 --> 00:54:37.230 align:middle line:84%
Anyth-- really, what
my dearest thing is,

00:54:37.230 --> 00:54:40.050 align:middle line:84%
I am here to help people
become the extraordinary selves

00:54:40.050 --> 00:54:40.960 align:middle line:90%
that they are.

00:54:40.960 --> 00:54:44.310 align:middle line:84%
And so I help artists and
entrepreneurs and visionaries

00:54:44.310 --> 00:54:47.740 align:middle line:84%
to really realize their highest
dream, whatever that is.

00:54:47.740 --> 00:54:49.140 align:middle line:90%
And so sometimes it is help--

00:54:49.140 --> 00:54:50.920 align:middle line:90%
I've helped a lot of people--

00:54:50.920 --> 00:54:51.880 align:middle line:90%
I do book coaching.

00:54:51.880 --> 00:54:52.680 align:middle line:90%
I--

00:54:52.680 --> 00:54:52.995 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Book coaching.

00:54:52.995 --> 00:54:53.795 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yeah.

00:54:53.795 --> 00:54:55.040 align:middle line:90%
I've done business coaching.

00:54:55.040 --> 00:54:56.670 align:middle line:84%
I do whatever you
pay me for, really.

00:54:56.670 --> 00:54:58.230 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:54:58.230 --> 00:54:59.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:54:59.190 --> 00:54:59.763 align:middle line:90%
Clean floors?

00:54:59.763 --> 00:55:00.050 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: No, not whatever.

00:55:00.050 --> 00:55:00.720 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Do you do windows?

00:55:00.720 --> 00:55:01.520 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: [LAUGHS]

00:55:01.520 --> 00:55:03.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What?

00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:06.390 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell me a little bit
of a success story of somebody

00:55:06.390 --> 00:55:10.380 align:middle line:84%
that you did work with, that
came from such a tiny place

00:55:10.380 --> 00:55:11.497 align:middle line:90%
into--

00:55:11.497 --> 00:55:13.080 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Just off
the top of my head,

00:55:13.080 --> 00:55:16.320 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking about a client who
is also an author, who did not

00:55:16.320 --> 00:55:17.513 align:middle line:90%
think she could write, ever.

00:55:17.513 --> 00:55:18.930 align:middle line:84%
Who did not think
she could write.

00:55:18.930 --> 00:55:22.620 align:middle line:84%
And she was a very
gifted psychotherapist,

00:55:22.620 --> 00:55:24.480 align:middle line:84%
and she wanted to
have a book out there.

00:55:24.480 --> 00:55:27.090 align:middle line:84%
And she kept hiring all
these ghost writers.

00:55:27.090 --> 00:55:28.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:55:28.470 --> 00:55:30.720 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And one of
them actually died,

00:55:30.720 --> 00:55:32.935 align:middle line:84%
and I was teasing her like,
oh, they became a ghost.

00:55:32.935 --> 00:55:34.044 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:55:34.044 --> 00:55:34.466 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh.

00:55:34.466 --> 00:55:35.310 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:55:35.310 --> 00:55:37.120 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: That's a
real ghost writer now.

00:55:37.120 --> 00:55:39.450 align:middle line:84%
But the point was, she
never believed she could

00:55:39.450 --> 00:55:40.650 align:middle line:90%
write or tell her own story.

00:55:40.650 --> 00:55:42.180 align:middle line:90%
And I kept bugging her.

00:55:42.180 --> 00:55:42.990 align:middle line:90%
Let's do this.

00:55:42.990 --> 00:55:44.130 align:middle line:90%
Let's get this out of you.

00:55:44.130 --> 00:55:45.930 align:middle line:90%
Let's you be you, right?

00:55:45.930 --> 00:55:49.440 align:middle line:84%
And she finally did,
and she did phenomenal.

00:55:49.440 --> 00:55:52.250 align:middle line:84%
Her books have done
better than mine.

00:55:52.250 --> 00:55:54.460 align:middle line:84%
It was just really
amazing to watch.

00:55:54.460 --> 00:55:57.810 align:middle line:84%
And so it was a great example
of, she was so shut down.

00:55:57.810 --> 00:55:59.640 align:middle line:84%
Like, there's no
way I could do this.

00:55:59.640 --> 00:56:00.790 align:middle line:90%
And I need experts, and I--

00:56:00.790 --> 00:56:00.960 align:middle line:90%
whatever.

00:56:00.960 --> 00:56:01.690 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm-hmm.

00:56:01.690 --> 00:56:04.200 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And again, I'm always
starting from the place of,

00:56:04.200 --> 00:56:05.910 align:middle line:84%
I never have an
answer for someone.

00:56:05.910 --> 00:56:07.680 align:middle line:90%
I don't know what the answer is.

00:56:07.680 --> 00:56:08.670 align:middle line:90%
I know how to find it.

00:56:08.670 --> 00:56:11.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You empower them to
find it within themselves.

00:56:11.100 --> 00:56:11.900 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Exactly.

00:56:11.900 --> 00:56:15.180 align:middle line:84%
Because I know there is a love
or an inspiration or something

00:56:15.180 --> 00:56:17.610 align:middle line:84%
that's speaking to that person,
and I'm following energy.

00:56:17.610 --> 00:56:20.450 align:middle line:84%
I'll follow-- I always follow
that inspired self in somebody.

00:56:20.450 --> 00:56:22.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you just
light it up for them.

00:56:22.200 --> 00:56:22.680 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:56:22.680 --> 00:56:23.550 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, we
don't really have

00:56:23.550 --> 00:56:24.680 align:middle line:84%
people like that
in our lives that

00:56:24.680 --> 00:56:26.760 align:middle line:84%
are going to be a constant
coaching cheerleader.

00:56:26.760 --> 00:56:27.560 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:56:27.560 --> 00:56:30.270 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I am
a witness to that.

00:56:30.270 --> 00:56:33.120 align:middle line:84%
And I wrote all of my
books to be the same thing,

00:56:33.120 --> 00:56:35.670 align:middle line:84%
because not everybody can
afford coaching, right?

00:56:35.670 --> 00:56:36.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:56:36.470 --> 00:56:39.060 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: And so I
wanted all of my books

00:56:39.060 --> 00:56:42.070 align:middle line:84%
to be like this coach in
your pocket that-- and people

00:56:42.070 --> 00:56:42.870 align:middle line:90%
tell me that.

00:56:42.870 --> 00:56:45.450 align:middle line:84%
That it's on their bed
stand, or they read it

00:56:45.450 --> 00:56:47.460 align:middle line:84%
in the mornings,
of just something

00:56:47.460 --> 00:56:49.980 align:middle line:84%
that, I'm going to
remind you consistently

00:56:49.980 --> 00:56:52.140 align:middle line:84%
how amazing you are, and
how extraordinary you

00:56:52.140 --> 00:56:53.750 align:middle line:90%
are, and don't settle.

00:56:53.750 --> 00:56:55.697 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do people
forget that that much?

00:56:55.697 --> 00:56:56.530 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Every day.

00:56:56.530 --> 00:56:57.210 align:middle line:90%
Every minute.

00:56:57.210 --> 00:56:57.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mm.

00:56:57.510 --> 00:56:57.630 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:56:57.630 --> 00:56:58.620 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: I do.

00:56:58.620 --> 00:56:59.420 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:56:59.420 --> 00:57:01.890 align:middle line:84%
I'm in this and I do,
because fear is so powerful,

00:57:01.890 --> 00:57:03.720 align:middle line:84%
and it takes over, and
we live in a culture

00:57:03.720 --> 00:57:05.512 align:middle line:84%
that we leave this
interview, and we're not

00:57:05.512 --> 00:57:07.637 align:middle line:84%
going to be hearing interviews
that are telling you

00:57:07.637 --> 00:57:08.593 align:middle line:90%
you're extraordinary.

00:57:08.593 --> 00:57:09.510 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, we're not.

00:57:09.510 --> 00:57:09.990 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: We're going
to be listening--

00:57:09.990 --> 00:57:10.800 align:middle line:90%
you'd better be careful.

00:57:10.800 --> 00:57:12.330 align:middle line:84%
And this and that,
and this and that.

00:57:12.330 --> 00:57:13.083 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What's wrong with you?

00:57:13.083 --> 00:57:13.270 align:middle line:90%
How come--

00:57:13.270 --> 00:57:14.603 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: What's wrong with you.

00:57:14.603 --> 00:57:15.650 align:middle line:90%
How to fix you.

00:57:15.650 --> 00:57:18.590 align:middle line:84%
And so again, I think
we need these voices.

00:57:18.590 --> 00:57:20.575 align:middle line:84%
It's my life's work,
is that I really

00:57:20.575 --> 00:57:22.950 align:middle line:84%
want to be this voice in the
world that will consistently

00:57:22.950 --> 00:57:25.110 align:middle line:84%
remind you of how
unparalleled you are.

00:57:25.110 --> 00:57:26.873 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you're
somebody's cheerleader.

00:57:26.873 --> 00:57:29.040 align:middle line:84%
You're really not going to
get that from your-- even

00:57:29.040 --> 00:57:31.082 align:middle line:84%
the people that love you
the most, because they--

00:57:31.082 --> 00:57:32.820 align:middle line:84%
as well-intentioned
as they may be,

00:57:32.820 --> 00:57:34.760 align:middle line:84%
they have a way of
saying it from--

00:57:34.760 --> 00:57:35.560 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Nagging.

00:57:35.560 --> 00:57:36.660 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:57:36.660 --> 00:57:37.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Good word.

00:57:37.460 --> 00:57:38.300 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: Let's
just say what it is.

00:57:38.300 --> 00:57:38.351 align:middle line:90%
No.

00:57:38.351 --> 00:57:39.768 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Let's just
say what it is.

00:57:39.768 --> 00:57:40.740 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, exactly.

00:57:40.740 --> 00:57:42.400 align:middle line:84%
So you've explained
this a little bit.

00:57:42.400 --> 00:57:44.020 align:middle line:84%
But in the overall
picture of things,

00:57:44.020 --> 00:57:46.450 align:middle line:90%
what is your biggest why?

00:57:46.450 --> 00:57:47.770 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: My biggest why?

00:57:47.770 --> 00:57:48.570 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:57:48.570 --> 00:57:50.190 align:middle line:90%
My biggest why, I think--

00:57:50.190 --> 00:57:55.530 align:middle line:84%
I always say that on my watch,
I don't want somebody giving up

00:57:55.530 --> 00:57:57.330 align:middle line:90%
on what they could have been.

00:57:57.330 --> 00:57:58.560 align:middle line:90%
I know my own life.

00:57:58.560 --> 00:58:03.210 align:middle line:10%
I know how unhappy and
how scared I've been,

00:58:03.210 --> 00:58:06.360 align:middle line:10%
and how many times I
have quit or almost

00:58:06.360 --> 00:58:09.810 align:middle line:10%
quit this path, and the
life I would have missed,

00:58:09.810 --> 00:58:12.570 align:middle line:10%
and the people I've touched,
and the journeys I've had

00:58:12.570 --> 00:58:13.927 align:middle line:10%
and continue to have.

00:58:13.927 --> 00:58:16.260 align:middle line:84%
I would have missed that, and
I don't want somebody else

00:58:16.260 --> 00:58:17.550 align:middle line:90%
to miss their life.

00:58:17.550 --> 00:58:20.160 align:middle line:84%
I deeply believe that there
are inventors out there right

00:58:20.160 --> 00:58:23.220 align:middle line:84%
now, or entrepreneurs,
or healers, or artists,

00:58:23.220 --> 00:58:27.240 align:middle line:84%
or leaders, or corporate leaders
that have brilliant ideas--

00:58:27.240 --> 00:58:29.190 align:middle line:84%
or doctors, or health
practitioners that

00:58:29.190 --> 00:58:31.530 align:middle line:90%
have something unconventional.

00:58:31.530 --> 00:58:35.320 align:middle line:84%
And on my watch, as
long as I'm alive,

00:58:35.320 --> 00:58:38.662 align:middle line:84%
I want to empower that for them
to trust what's inside them,

00:58:38.662 --> 00:58:39.870 align:middle line:90%
and to go to that next level.

00:58:39.870 --> 00:58:43.350 align:middle line:84%
Because I deeply believe they
have genius to give this world,

00:58:43.350 --> 00:58:44.760 align:middle line:90%
and I want them to give it.

00:58:44.760 --> 00:58:46.110 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: To show it back to them.

00:58:46.110 --> 00:58:46.410 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:58:46.410 --> 00:58:47.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And to find
out themselves.

00:58:47.140 --> 00:58:47.940 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:58:47.940 --> 00:58:50.280 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And also, finding
it yourself, or myself,

00:58:50.280 --> 00:58:52.783 align:middle line:84%
if you're the coach, is
so much more impactful

00:58:52.783 --> 00:58:55.200 align:middle line:84%
than someone else saying, you
need to do this, this, this,

00:58:55.200 --> 00:58:56.026 align:middle line:90%
and five steps to this.

00:58:56.026 --> 00:58:56.790 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: It doesn't work.

00:58:56.790 --> 00:58:56.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:58:56.990 --> 00:58:58.920 align:middle line:84%
>>KIEVES: You will not stay
with somebody else's steps.

00:58:58.920 --> 00:59:00.420 align:middle line:84%
You will only stay
with your own,

00:59:00.420 --> 00:59:01.750 align:middle line:90%
because you need to be moved.

00:59:01.750 --> 00:59:02.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:59:02.550 --> 00:59:04.590 align:middle line:84%
Well, thank you so
much for showing us

00:59:04.590 --> 00:59:07.710 align:middle line:84%
what it means to thrive
through uncertainty.

00:59:07.710 --> 00:59:11.280 align:middle line:84%
And it seems like really just
to find that inner inspiration,

00:59:11.280 --> 00:59:13.000 align:middle line:84%
and that helps you
get through anything.

00:59:13.000 --> 00:59:13.800 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Yes.

00:59:13.800 --> 00:59:15.430 align:middle line:84%
Thank you so much
for the work you do.

00:59:15.430 --> 00:59:16.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:59:16.230 --> 00:59:16.650 align:middle line:90%
>>KIEVES: Thank you.

00:59:16.650 --> 00:59:17.610 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

